al by [[Antipope John XXIII]] on 6 June 1411, long after he had been transferred to the diocese of Lisbon. Eubel, I, pp. 33 no. 4.  Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 148-152.</ref>||&nbsp;||15 February 1391||1398<ref>Joannes Alfonso Estevez de Zambuya was transferred to the diocese of Coimbra on 23 September 1398; he undertook his financial obligations to the Apostolic Chamber on 25 February 1399. Eubel, I, pp. 196, 406.</ref>||23 January 1415<ref>Azambuja had been Bishop of Lisbon since 29 May 1402. Eubel, I, p. 507.</ref>\n|}\n\n===from 1400 to 1700===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!#!!Name!!Date of Birth!!Appointed!!Retired!!Date of Death\n|-\n||37||[[Gil Alma]]||&nbsp;||6 August 1399||1407||1415\n|-\n||38||[[Jo\u00e3o V Afonso Aranha]]||&nbsp;||1407||1414||&nbsp;\n|-\n||39||[[Fernando III Guerra]]||1390||18 June 1414<ref>Fernardo Guerra was appointed by [[Antipope John XXIII|John XXIII]] on 18 June 1414. Eubel, I, p. 407.</ref>||15 December 1417<ref>Guerra was transferred to the Archbishopric of Braga by [[Pope Martin V]] on 15 December 1417.</ref>||26 September 1467<ref>Eubel, II, p. 110, note 1.</ref>\n|-\n\n||39a||[[Joannes Alfonsi]]||&nbsp;||26 January 1418<ref>Joannes Alfonsi was appointed by Pope Martin V, but he resigned while still Bishop-elect. Eubel, I, p. 407.</ref>||?||&nbsp;\n|-\n\n||40||[[Vasco II (bishop of Porto)|Vasco Petri]]||&nbsp;||2 April 1421<ref>Vasco Petri, ''Doctor in utroque iure'' (Civil and Canon Law), was approved as Bishop of Porto by [[Pope Martin V]] on 2 April 1421.</ref>||1423<ref>Bishop Vasco was transferred to the diocese of Evora on 10 March 1423, the same day that Antonio de Chaves was appointed his successor at Porto. There is no room for a Bishop Durandus. Eubel, I, p. 236.</ref>||1428\n|-\n||41||'''[[Ant\u00f3nio Martins de Chaves]]'''<ref>Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 163-165. He was created a cardinal by [[Pope Eugene IV]] on 18 December 1439. Eubel, II, p. 8 no. 14. He had been in Italy for the C