pe Urban VIII]].</ref>||3 January 1643<ref>Da Cunha had been transferred to the diocese of Lisbon on 3 December 1635. He died on 3 January 1643. Gauchat, p. 352, with note 5. </ref>\n|-\n||58||[[Jo\u00e3o VII de Valadares]], O.E.S.A.||&nbsp;||30 August 1627<ref>Valadares was transferred from the diocese of Miranda in the Consistory of 30 August 1627 by [[Pope Urban VIII]]. Gauchat, IV, p. 245 with note 8; 286 with note 5.</ref>||23 May 1635||23 May 1635&nbsp;\n|-\n||59||[[Gaspar do Rego da Fonseca]]||&nbsp;||9 June 1636<ref>Rego de Fonseca was transferred from the titular See of Targensis Africa (He was auxiliary bishop of Lisbon) in the Consistory of 9 June 1636 by Pope Urban VIII. Gauchat, IV, p. 286 with note 6; 327 with note 3..</ref>||13 July 1639||13 July 1639&nbsp;\n|-\n|colspan=6 align=center bgcolor=#FFFFE0|''Vacant see (1640\u20131670)''\n|-\n||<center>X</center>||[[Francisco Pereira Pinto]]<ref>Pereira was nominated on 31 October 1640, but never received his bulls of consecration and installation. He was never consecrated a bishop. Gauchat, IV, p. 286 with note 7.</ref>||bgcolor=#eee colspan=4 align=center|''Nominated in 1640 by [[Philip III of Portugal]] but did not receive approval from [[Pope Urban VIII]].''\n|-\n||<center>X</center>||[[Sebasti\u00e3o C\u00e9sar de Menezes]]||bgcolor=#eee colspan=4 align=center rowspan=3|''Nominated in 1641, 1659, and 1669 by [[John IV of Portugal]], but not approved by the Pope''\n|-\n||<center>X</center>||[[Pedro VII de Menezes]]\n|-\n||<center>X</center>||[[Luis de Souza]]\n|-\n||60||[[Nicolau Monteiro]]||December 1581<ref>Born in Porto, Nicolas Monteiro was the son of Don Nicolas Velho and Do\u00f1a Maria de Monteyro. He held a doctorate in Canon Law (Coimbra). Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, p. 221.</ref>||15 December 1670<ref>Ritzler-Sefrin, V, p. 322. He was consecrated a bishop on 31 May 1671, by the titular Bishop of Sidon, [[Francesco Ravizza]].</ref>||20 December 1672||20 December 1672<ref>Almeida,