y league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen1 = [[Jim Rukutai]] 2\n| try2 = Hutton\n| con2 = Dufty\n| pen2 = Dufty 3 & 1 mark\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee =\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 18 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = North Shore\n| score = 2-30\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Cup Matches Begin/North Shore V Newton\n| page =6\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16854\n| date = 1918-05-20\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180520.2.78\n| accessdate = 2019-08-18}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 = Phil Castles, Keenan, Lovett, Thomas, unknown x 4\n| con1 = Len Farrant, unknown x 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Parker\n| stadium = Devonport Domain\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Round 2===\nNorth Shore lost by default to Maritime. In the City v Grafton match the City player Mitchell was ordered off by referee Vause for disputing a decision. He wrote a letter of apology during the week and the league ordered him to appear on Saturday to receive a \u201csevere citation\u201d <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Northern Union Meeting of Executive\n| page = 2\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 128\n| date = 1918-05-30\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19180530.2.14\n| accessdate = 2020-02-04}}</ref>\n\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 8-7\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Championship Matches/Newton V Ponsonby\n| page =7\n| publisher =New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16860\n| date = 1918-05-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180527.2.62.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-18}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = W Southernwood, E McGregor\n| con1 = M Maddison\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Keenan\n| con2 = [[Bill Williams (rugby league)|Bill Williams]]\n| pen2 = Phil Castles\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance =\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 May\n| time =