-11\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Under League Rules/Maritime Defeats Grafton\n| page =3\n| publisher =New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16932\n| date = 1918-08-19\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180819.2.9.3\n| accessdate = 2019-08-18}}</ref>| away = Grafton\n| try1 = Hogg, [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]], Lunn 2\n| con1 = Stallworthy, Dufty\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Karl Ifwersen]]\n| con2 = T Taylor\n| pen2 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 3\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Semi Final===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Maritime\n| score = 13-8\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =The Roope Rooster Contest/Maritime Wins Semi-Final\n| page =2\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16938\n| date = 1918-08-26\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180826.2.4.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 = Tom Sheehan, Hogg, Dufty\n| con1 = Stallworthy\n| pen1 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]\n| try2 = Miller, Keenan\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = A Isles\n| stadium = Auckland Domain\n| attendance = 5500\n| referee = A Ball\n}}\n \n===Final===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 6-3\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =\u201dRoope Rooster\u201d Final/City Wins From Maritime\n| page =7\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 209\n| date = 1918-09-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19180902.2.53\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Maritime\n| try1 = Maurice Wetherill, B Paki\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = W Wynyard\n}}\n\n==Top Try Scorers and Point Scorers==\nThe following point scoring lists include both Senior Championship matches (including preliminary rounds) and the Roope Rooster competition. For the 5th time in 6 seasons [[Karl Ifwersen]] topped the point scoring lists with 66 points. This gave him 287 points from 6 seasons. While E McGregor of Ponsonby United topped the try scoring list with 10. Newton Rangers had 4 tries and 2 conversions unattributed while Ponsonby had 1 try unattributed which make the point lists for those teams slightly incomplete.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Player!!Team!!Tries\n|-\n|1||E McGregor||Ponsonby United||10\n|-\n|2||Keenan||Newton Rangers||8\n|-\n|3||H Simpson||Grafton Athletic||5\n|-\n|3||C Mitchell||City Rovers||5\n|-\n|5||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||4\n|-\n|5||George Isles||Newton Rangers||4\n|-\n|5||Thomas||Newton Rangers||4\n|-\n|5||R Clarke||City Rovers||4\n|-\n|5||A Rae||Ponsonby United||4\n|-\n|5||[[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]||Maritime||4\n|-\n|5||Hogg||Maritime||4\n|-\n|5||[[Karl Ifwersen]]||Grafton Athletic||4\n|-\n|5||Tremain||Grafton Athletic||4\n|-\n|5||[[Dougie McGregor]]||Grafton Athletic||4\n|-\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Player!!Team!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Mark!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Karl Ifwersen]]||Grafton Athletic||4||11||16||0||66\n|-\n|2||M Maddison||Ponsonby United||1||16||6||1||49\n|-\n|3||Dufty||Maritime||2||3||7||2||30\n|-\n|3||E McGregor||Ponsonby United||10||0||0||0||30\n|-\n|5||Keenan||Newton Rangers||8||1||0||0||26\n|-\n|6||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||4||4||2||0||24\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Thacker Shield==\n[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] travelled south to [[Christchurch]] to play a match with [[Sydenham, New Zealand|Sydenham]] for the [[Thacker Shield]]. They were victorious and brought the shield to [[Auckland]].\n\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Sydenham\n| score = 0-11\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby Beats Sydenham/Eleven Points to Nil\n| page =7\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16944\n| date = 1918-09-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180902.2.57.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = \n| con1 =\n| pen1 = \n| try2 = A Rae, [[Bill Walsh (rugby league)|Bill Walsh]], [[Arthur Matthews (rugby league)|Arthur Matthews]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = M Maddison\n| stadium = Sydenham Park, Christchurch\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n==Lower Grade Clubs==\nThe lower grades featured teams in the 2nd grade (5), 3rd grade (5), 4th grade (9), 5th grade (11), and 6th grade (4).<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Northern Union/The Last Preliminaries\n| page =7 \n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 113\n| date = 1918-05-13\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19180513.2.65\n| accessdate = 2019-08-18}}</ref>\n*Big Store\n*Mangere\n*[[Manukau Magpies|Manukau]]\n*[[Northcote Tigers|Northcote Ramblers]]\n*[[Otahuhu Leopards|Otahuhu]]\n*Parnell\n*[[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond Rovers]]\n*Sunnyside (based in Devonport)\n*[[Post and Telegraph]]\n*Thames Old Boys\n\n==Exhibition Matches==\nRichmond and the Post and Telegraph 4th grade teams traveled to Thames to play an exhibition match on the 12th of October. Post and Telegraph had been winners of the championship with Richmond the runners up.\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | List of Exhibition Matches\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Exhibition Match\n| 12 Oct <ref>{{cite news \n| title =New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16980\n| page =3 \n| publisher = \n| date = 1918-10-14\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19181014.2.13.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n|| Post and Telegraph || 12 || Richmond || 10 || Thames \n|-\n|}\n\n==Representative Fixtures==\nOn the 7th of September a trial match was held between two teams picked by the selectors at [[Victoria Park, New Zealand|Victoria Park]] in order to select the Auckland representative team. The A team was Minogue, [[Bill Walsh (rugby league)|Bill Walsh]], [[Thomas McClymont]], Clarke (Ponsonby), McGregor, [[Karl Ifwersen]], Bailey, [[Ernie Herring]] (Grafton), [[George Isles]] (Newton), Davidson (Maritime), [[Jim Rukutai]], Haddon, Francis (City, while the B Team was [[George Paki]], [[Ivan Stewart (rugby league)|Ivan Stewart]] (City), McGregor, Maddison, Cadman (Ponsonby), Thomas, Keenan, [[Bill Williams (rugby league)|Bill Williams]] (Newton), Pullen, Simpson (Grafton), Avery, Cross, Sheehan (Maritime), with Hanlin (Ponsonby), Stallworthy (Maritime), Clarke (City), and Keenan (Newton) named in the reserves. The following weekend [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] played [[Canterbury rugby league team|Canterbury]] at the [[Auckland Domain]] and were victorious by 45 points to 9. \n\n===Trial Match===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = A Team\n| score = 36-15\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Selector\u2019s Test Match/Auckland Team Chosen\n| page =3\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16950\n| date = 1918-09-09\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180909.2.13.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = B Team\n| try1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2, Clarke, [[Karl Ifwersen]], [[Dougie McGregor]], unknown x 7 points\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2, [[Dougie McGregor]] 2, Phil Castles\n| pen1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]], Phil Castles\n| try2 = Mitchell, Thomas, [[Bert Avery]]\n| con2 = Keenan\n| pen2 = Keenan\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Murray\n}}\n\n===Auckland v Canterbury===\nThe match saw 10,000 spectators attend and took in 300 pounds in gate takings.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 14 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 45-9\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland Defeats Canterbury/Forty-Five Points to Nine\n| page =3\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16956\n| date = 1918-09-16\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180916.2.15.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Canterbury\n| try1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 5, [[Karl Ifwersen]] 2, Haddon 2, George Isles, [[Thomas McClymont]]\n| con1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 4, Phil Castles, Ernie Bailey\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = unknown\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Mitchell, Smythe 2 marks\n| stadium = Auckland Domain\n| attendance = 10000\n| referee = A Ball\n}}\n\n===Auckland Representative Matches Played and Scorers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!No!!Name!!Club Team!!Play!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||1||5||0||0||15\n|-\n|2||[[Karl Ifwersen]]||Grafton Athletic||1||2||4||0||14\n|-\n|3||Haddon||City Rovers||1||2||0||0||6\n|-\n|4||George Isles||Newton Rangers||1||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|4||[[Thomas McClymont]]||Ponsonby United||1||1||0||0||3\n|-\n|6||Phil Castles||Newton Rangers||1||0||1||0||2\n|-\n|6||Ernie Bailey||Grafton Athletic*||1||0||0||0||2\n|-\n|8||Paki||City Rovers||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|8||[[Dougie McGregor]]||Grafton Athletic||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|8||[[Bill Walsh (rugby league)|Bill Walsh]]||Ponsonby United||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|8||[[Jim Rukutai]]||City Rovers||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|8||[[Bill Williams (rugby league)|Bill Williams]]||Newton Rangers||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|8||[[Ernie Herring]]||Grafton Athletic||1||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|}\n\nErnie Bailey had begun the season with North Shore but after they withdrew their senior team from the competition he transferred to the Grafton Athletic team.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.aucklandleague.co.nz/ Auckland Rugby League Official Site]\n\n[[Category:Auckland Rugby League seasons]]\n[[Category:Rugby league in Auckland]]\n[[Category:Rugby league governing bodies in New Zealand]] \n[[Category:Rugby league]]\n|}\n", "text_old": "The 1918 [[Auckland Rugby League]] season was its 10th since its inception in 1909. It was again severely affected by the ongoing war with several hundred players serving overseas and 44 killed who were named in the annual report.<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Review of Last Season\n| page =7 \n| publisher =New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16812 \n| date = 1918-04-01\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180401.2.73\n| accessdate = 2020-01-26}}</ref> [[North Shore Albions]] withdrew from the competition early in the season and on other occasions teams played short-handed. There was also a truncated representative program with only a trial match and one full [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] representative match versus [[Canterbury rugby league team|Canterbury]], which was played at the [[Auckland Domain]] in front of 10,000 spectators.\n\nThe senior grade featured six teams. [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] won their second consecutive title with an 8-win\u20131-loss record. Ponsonby then traveled to Christchurch to play Sydenham for the Thacker Shield and they won 11 points to 0. [[City Rovers]] won their second Roope Rooster title with a 6\u20133 win over Maritime following their first win in 1916.\n\nSenior games still regularly attracted strong crowds. The round 4 matches at [[Victoria Park, Auckland|Victoria Park]] drew an estimated crowd of 6,000.<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Ponsonby Beats City/Ponsonby V City/Maritime V Newton\n| page =8 \n| publisher =New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16866 \n| date = 1918-06-10\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180603.2.108.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-18}}</ref> While 4,000 attended the round 5 matches, 5,000 the round 7 clash between [[City Rovers]] and [[Grafton Athletic]] at the same venue,<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Newton Defeats Grafton\n| page =3\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 149\n| date = 1918-06-24\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19180624.2.20\n| accessdate = 2019-08-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite news \n| title =City Defeats Grafton\n| page =7 \n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16896\n| date = 1918-06-08\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19180708.2.50\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref> and 6,000 witnessed the round 9 match between [[City Rovers]] and [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]].\n\nAt the season end many one off matches were played between various teams. One of the more notable ones was a match between the [[Auckland Star]] staff and the [[New Zealand Herald]] staff. The game was won by the Auckland Star by 8 points to 4.<ref>{{cite news \n| title =\u201dStar\u201d V \u201cHerald\u201d\n| page =3\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 233\n| date = 1918-09-30\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19180930.2.22\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref> These company type fixtures were to become a regular feature of Auckland Rugby League for decades to come.\n\n{{s-start}}\n        {{s-bef|before=[[1917 Auckland Rugby League season|1917]]}}\n        {{s-ttl|title=10th [[Auckland Rugby League]] season\n        |years=1918}}\n        {{s-aft|after=[[1919 Auckland Rugby League season|1919]]}}\n        {{end}}\n\n===Maritime, Mangere, and Big Store Football Clubs join the league===\nThe Maritime club applied to join the Auckland Rugby League with the nomination of a senior team. This was accepted by the league.<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Auckland Rugby League/Meeting of Committee\n| page =7\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 86\n| date = 1918-04-11\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19180411.2.84\n| accessdate = 2020-01-26}}</ref> They finished the season with a 1 win, 7 loss record.\n\nThe Mangere club applied for affiliation and the registration of 23 players at the Auckland Rugby League meeting on April 17. This was granted by the league. They were to play in maroon and gold originally as requested but before the season started asked to wear blue instead.\n\nThe Big Store Football Club nominated a team to play in the league which was accepted and their colours of blue and white were approved.<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Auckland Rugby League\n| page =2\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 92\n| date = 1918-04-18\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19180418.2.15\n| accessdate = 2020-01-26}}</ref>\n\n===New League Rooms===\nAt the conclusion of the season the league opened their own league rooms on Swanson Street. The rooms were used for the first time with the Auckland Rugby League executive meeting on 23 October. The rooms consisted of \"a large billiard room and League office, and a room for clubs to hold their weekly meetings in\". It was stated that players did not formerly meet \"their fellow players during the summer time, but with this club now on a sound footing they will be able to meet each other and spend enjoyable evenings which should bring about a better feeling between the different teams\".<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Auckland Rugby League Meeting of Executive\n| page =6\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume XLIX, Issue 254\n| date = 1918-02-03\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19181024.2.72\n| accessdate = 2020-01-26}}</ref>\n\n===Representative Match===\nAuckland played a representative match for the first time in a few seasons. They had taken a hiatus during the war years but they played a trial match between and A and B team before a match with Canterbury at the Auckland Domain. The match attracted an enormous crowd of 10,000 and Auckland won easily by 45 points to 9.\n\n==First Grade Championship==\nThe season began with 2 preliminary rounds before the competitions began proper on the 18th of May. Around 5,000 spectators attended the first round matches at [[Victoria Park, New Zealand|Victoria Park]] and Devonport Domain. [[North Shore Albions]] played the preliminary rounds, round 1, and defaulted their next two matches before withdrawing from the competition.\n\n===Teams===\nThe competition featured 6 teams.\n*[[City Rovers]] (red and black)\n*[[Grafton Athletic]] (black and white)\n*Maritime (white)\n*[[Newton Rangers]] (red and white)\n*[[North Shore Albions]] (green and white)\n*[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] (blue and black)\n\n===Final Standings===\n{|\n|-\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"For\" |F\n!width=20 abbr=\"Against\" |A\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[ Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n|9||8||0||1||103||53||'''16'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Newton Rangers]]\n|9||7||0||2||123||37||'''14'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[City Rovers]]\n|8||5||0||3||73||85||'''10'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Grafton Athletic]]\n|8||2||0||6||94||125||'''4'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|Maritime\n|8||1||0||8||45||110||'''2'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[North Shore Albions]]\n|3||0||0||3||2||30||'''0'''\n|-\n|}\n[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] and Maritime both had default wins over [[North Shore Albions]]. Newton had a default win over Maritime (R9). These results are included in the standings.\n\n===Preliminary Round 1===\nNorth Shore was struggling to field a team owing to the impact of the war on their playing numbers. They only managed 11 players for their match with Maritime who were also fielding a weakened forward pack.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Newton\n| score = 15-8\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Newton V City\n| page =3\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LV, Issue 16842\n| date = 1918-05-06\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/