\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q41173|c=category:Demi Lovato|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|s=no|wikt=no|species=no}}\n*{{Official website}}\n*{{IMDb name|1416215|Demi Lovato}}\n\n{{Demi Lovato|state=expanded}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = [[List of awards and nominations received by Demi Lovato|Awards for Demi Lovato]]\n| list =\n{{GLAAD Vanguard Award}}\n{{MTV Video Music Award for Best Video with a Social Message}}\n}}\n\n{{Portalbar|Biography|Pop music|Television|Film|United States}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lovato, Demi}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Activists from Texas]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Dallas]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American Christians]]\n[[Category:American contemporary R&B singers]]\n[[Category:American female pop singers]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American female rock singers]]\n[[Category:American feminists]]\n[[Category:American philanthropists]]\n[[Category:American pop rock singers]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American women activists]]\n[[Category:American musicians of Mexican descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:Anti-bullying activists]]\n[[Category:Demi Lovato| ]]\n[[Category:Child pop musicians]]\n[[Category:Feminist musicians]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American female singers]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records artists]]\n[[Category:Island Records artists]]\n[[Category:LGBT rights activists from the United States]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mental health activists]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Albuquerque, New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Dallas]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People with bipolar disorder]]\n[[Category:Republic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Safehouse Records artists]]\n[[Category:Singers from New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Singers from Texas]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from New Mexico]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from Texas]]\n[[Category:American child singers]]\n[[Category:LGBT musicians from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT singers from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from New Mexico]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Texas]]\n[[Category:LGBT women]]\n[[Category:LGBT women's culture]]\n[[Category:LGBT actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-semi|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American singer, actress, and author}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Demi Lovato\n| image              = Demi Lovato Interview Feb 2020.png\n| caption            = Lovato during an interview in 2020\n| birth_name         = Demetria Devonne Lovato\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1992|8|20}}\n| birth_place        = [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]], U.S.<ref>[https://www.biography.com/musician/demi-lovato Demi Lovato - Age, Songs & Movies - Biography<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n| residence          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/dirt/real-estalker/demi-lovato-laurel-canyon-home-landslide-1201974654/|title=Demi Lovato's Laurel Canyon Home Unsafe For Entry After Landslide|website=Variety|first=Mark|last=David|date=January 31, 2017|accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref>\n| relatives          = [[Madison De La Garza]] (half-sister)\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*Singer\n*songwriter\n*actress\n*television personality\n*activist\n*author\n}}\n| years_active       = 2002\u2013present<ref name=\"nydailynews1\">{{cite news|last=Bitette |first=Nicole |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/demi-lovato-break-music-spotlight-article-1.2817487 |title=Demi Lovato is taking a break from music and the spotlight |newspaper=New York Daily News |date=October 4, 2016 |accessdate=December 8, 2016}}</ref>\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Demi Lovato|Full list]]\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background   = solo_singer\n| genre        = <!--Do not add any additional genres without a source. Genres sourced below.-->{{flatlist|\n*[[Pop music|Pop]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sputnikmusic.com/bands/Demi-Lovato/12763/ |title=Demi Lovato reviews, music, news |publisher=sputnikmusic |date=May 14, 2013 |accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[pop rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.excite.com/events/concert-tickets/Demi-Lovato/Demi-Lovato-Anaheim-CA/index.php |title=Demi Lovato Anaheim Tickets |publisher=Excite.com |date= |accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Jocelyn Vena |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1644100/demi-lovato-wants-to-embrace-her-inner-soul-diva-on-next-album/ |title=Demi Lovato Wants To Embrace Her 'Inner Soul' Diva On Next Album |publisher=MTV |date=July 20, 2010 |accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reverbnation.com/demilovato |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121095637/https://www.reverbnation.com/demilovato |url-status=dead |archive-date=January 21, 2016 |title=Demi Lovato &#124; ReverbNation |date= |accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n| instrument  = {{flatlist|\n*Vocals\n*guitar\n*piano\n}}\n| label      = {{flatlist|\n*[[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n*[[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]]\n*[[Island Records|Island]]\n*[[Safehouse Records|Safehouse]]\n}}\n| associated_acts = [[Jonas Brothers]]\n}}\n| website            = {{URL|demilovato.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Demetria Devonne <!--Wikipedia policy states that it should just say \"Demetria Devonne Lovato\", not \"Demetria Devonne 'Demi' Lovato\", as although she has stated that she hates being referred to as \"Demetria\", \"Demi\" isn't short for anything else--> Lovato''' ({{IPAc-en|l|\u0259|\u02c8|v|\u0251\u02d0|t|o\u028a}} {{respell|l\u0259|VAH|toh}}; born August 20, 1992) is an American singer, songwriter, actress, and television personality. She began her career in 2002 appearing on the children's television series ''[[Barney & Friends]]'', before rising to prominence for portraying Mitchie Torres in the [[Disney Channel]] musical television film ''[[Camp Rock]]'' (2008) and its sequel ''[[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam]]'' (2010).\n\nLovato has released six studio albums: ''[[Don't Forget]]'' (2008), [[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato album)|''Here We Go Again'']] (2009), [[Unbroken (Demi Lovato album)|''Unbroken'']] (2011), [[Demi (album)|''Demi'']] (2013), [[Confident (album)|''Confident'']] (2015), and [[Tell Me You Love Me (album)|''Tell Me You Love Me'']] (2017); all of which debuted in the top five of the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. She has earned nine top-20 tracks on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] with \"[[This Is Me (Demi Lovato song)|This Is Me]]\", \"[[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato song)|Here We Go Again]]\", \"[[Send It On (Disney's Friends for Change song)|Send It On]]\", \"[[Skyscraper (song)|Skyscraper]]\", \"[[Give Your Heart a Break]]\", \"[[Heart Attack (Demi Lovato song)|Heart Attack]]\", \"[[Cool for the Summer]]\", \"[[Sorry Not Sorry (Demi Lovato song)|Sorry Not Sorry]]\", and \"[[I Love Me (song)|I Love Me]]\". In total, she has sold over two million albums and 20 million singles in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7998706/demi-lovato-21-savage-tom-petty-ask-billboard|title=Ask Billboard: Demi Lovato's Career Album & Song Sales|website=Billboard|access-date=December 13, 2019|date=October 15, 2017}}</ref> On television, Lovato has starred as the titular character on ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'' (2009\u20132011), served as a judge and mentor on [[The X Factor (American TV series)|''The X Factor USA'']] in its [[The X Factor (American season 2)|second]] and [[The X Factor (American season 3)|third]] seasons, and appeared as a recurring character on [[Glee (TV series)|''Glee'']]. Her struggles with several personal issues received significant media attention in the 2010s; in response to which she published the book ''Staying Strong: 365 Days a Year'' (2013) and released a [[YouTube]] documentary about her life and career, titled ''[[Demi Lovato: Simply Complicated]]'' (2017).\n\nLovato is a [[Pop music|pop]], [[pop rock]], and [[R&B]] artist. She has earned numerous [[List of awards and nominations received by Demi Lovato|awards and nominations]], including an [[MTV Video Music Award]], 14 [[Teen Choice Awards]], five [[People's Choice Awards]], and two [[Latin American Music Awards]]. She also holds one ''[[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]]'' and was included on the annual [[Time 100|''Time'' 100]] list of the most influential people in the world in 2017. Outside the entertainment industry, Lovato is an activist for several social causes.\n\n==Life and career==\n===1992\u20132006: Early life and career beginnings===\nLovato was born on August 20, 1992 in [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]]<!--SEE TALK BEFORE CHANGING TO DALLAS --><ref name=\"BioChannelBiography\">{{cite web|url=http://www.biography.com/people/demi-lovato-481444|title=Demi Lovato Biography \u2013 Facts, Birthday, Life Story|publisher=[[The Biography Channel]]. [[A+E Networks]]|accessdate=March 10, 2013}}</ref> to former [[Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders|Dallas Cowboys cheerleader]] Dianna De La Garza (n\u00e9e Dianna Lee Smith)<ref name=MotherLine>{{cite web|title=SUE EMMONS and DONALD SMITH|url=http://familytreemaker.genealogy.com/users/h/a/r/Sue-D-Hart-Ar/GENE3-0008.html|publisher=Family Tree Maker}}</ref> and engineer and musician Patrick Martin Lovato.<ref name=PatrickDeathBillboard>{{cite web|last=Payne|first=Chris|title=Demi Lovato's Father Dies|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1568025/demi-lovatos-father-passes-away|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=June 22, 2013}}</ref> She has an older sister named Dallas;<ref name=\"DallasBirthday\">{{cite web|title=Happy 24th Birthday Dallas Lovato February 4, 2012 |url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/02/04/happy-24th-birthday-dallas-lovato-february-4-2012/ |publisher=Disney Dreaming |accessdate=February 4, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208061154/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/02/04/happy-24th-birthday-dallas-lovato-february-4-2012/ |archivedate=February 8, 2012 }}</ref> a younger maternal half-sister, actress [[Madison De La Garza]];<ref name=\"WP\">{{cite news|first=Laura|last=Yao|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/06/20/AR2008062003077_pf.html|title=Disney Demi-Goddess|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=June 21, 2008|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> and an older paternal half-sister named Amber, whom she first spoke to when she was 20.<ref name=\"amber-lovato\">{{cite magazine|title=Demi Lovato Reveals Secret Half-Sister|url=https://people.com/celebrity/demi-lovato-has-a-30-year-old-half-sister/|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=March 6, 2013|accessdate=April 3, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170404013116/http://people.com/celebrity/demi-lovato-has-a-30-year-old-half-sister/|archivedate=April 4, 2017}}</ref>\n\nLovato's parents divorced in mid-1994, shortly after her second birthday.<ref name=Chance>{{cite book|first=Jody|last=Jensen Shaffer|title=Demi Lovato: Taking Another Chance|year=2013|publisher=Lerner Publications|location=Minneapolis, Minnesota|isbn=978-1467715515|page=7}}</ref> Lovato's father was of [[Mexicans|Mexican]] descent, with mostly [[Spaniards|Spanish]] and [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] ancestors, and came from a family that has been living in New Mexico for generations; he also had distant [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] and [[Jewish]] ancestry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5xMrNnZ21Ck|title=Demi Lovato finds out she's Jewish!?|last=KISS FM UK|date=September 22, 2015|publisher=|accessdate=March 10, 2017|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref name=\"Hispanic Hollywood\">{{cite news|title=The Hollywood Reporter Names the Young Hispanic Hollywood Class of 2013|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/demi-lovato-658894|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=November 22, 2013|date=November 22, 2013|quote=In honor of her Mexican-American father,}}</ref> Her mother is of [[English people|English]] and [[Irish people|Irish]] ancestry.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nicola|last=Murphy|url=https://www.irishcentral.com/culture/entertainment/how-irish-ancestry-links-demi-lovato-megan-fox-and-olivia-wilde-photos-213964591-237761091|title=How Irish ancestry links Demi Lovato, Megan Fox and Olivia Wilde|website=Irish Central|date=March 15, 2014|accessdate=August 26, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/ddlovato/status/267890338557992960|title=Twitter|website=mobile.twitter.com|accessdate=August 23, 2017}}</ref> Through her father, Lovato is a descendant of [[American Civil War|Civil War]] [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] veteran [[Francisco Perea]] and [[Santa Fe de Nuevo M\u00e9xico]] governor [[Francisco Xavier Ch\u00e1vez]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.somosprimos.com/sp2010/spjun10/spjun10.htm|title=Somos Primos|publisher=Diario El Carabobe\u00f1o|accessdate=October 5, 2013}}</ref> Lovato claims that through DNA testing she discovered that she is also of 16 percent [[North Germanic peoples|Scandinavian]] descent and one percent of African descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.refinery29.com/2017/02/142654/demi-lovato-one-percent-african|title=Demi Lovato Says She's 1% African|work=[[Refinery29]]|last=Smith|first=Courtney|date=February 26, 2017|accessdate=February 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nLovato was raised in [[Dallas]], Texas.<ref name=\"Biography Today\">{{cite book|title=Biography Today|year=2009|page=[https://archive.org/details/biographytodaypr0000unse/page/103 103]|publisher=Omnigraphics|location=Detroit, Michigan|isbn=978-0-7808-1052-5|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/biographytodaypr0000unse/page/103}}</ref><ref name=\"ref091\">{{cite news|first=Jon|last=Caramanica|title=Tween Princess, Tweaked|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=July 15, 2009|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/19/arts/music/19cara.html|accessdate=November 4, 2009}}</ref> She began playing [[piano]] at age seven and [[guitar]] at ten,<ref>\"Biography Today\", p.105</ref> when she also began dancing and acting classes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/this-is-how-i-made-it-ep-6-demi-lovato-and-bob/1698279/playlist.jhtml|title=Demi Lovato and B.o.B.|date=December 18, 2012|website=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141115114500/http://www.mtv.com/videos/this-is-how-i-made-it-ep-6-demi-lovato-and-bob/1698279/playlist.jhtml|archivedate=November 15, 2014|url-status=dead|accessdate=March 7, 2013}}</ref> In 2002, she began her career on the children's television series ''[[Barney & Friends]]'', portraying the role of Angela.<ref name=Barney>{{cite web|url=http://kidstvmovies.about.com/od/camprock/a/demilovato.htm|title=Demi Lovato The Disney Star Machine Does It Again|first=Carey|last=Bryson|website=[[About.com]]|publisher=[[IAC (company)|IAC]]|location=New York City|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> Lovato told [[Ellen DeGeneres]] that due to her acting career she was [[bullying|bullied]] so harshly that she asked for [[homeschooling]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/demi-lovato-rehab-dad-blames-hollywood-acting-issues-article-1.451886|title=Demi Lovato in rehab: Dad blames Hollywood, acting for her issues|first=Caroline|last=Culbertson|work=[[New York Daily News]]|date=November 2, 2010|accessdate=March 10, 2013}}</ref> and received her high-school diploma through homeschooling in May 2009, one year early.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2009/04/23/demi-lovato-graduates-high-school/ |title=Demi Lovato Graduates High School |website=[[Disney Dreaming]]|publisher=[[Walt Disney Company]]|location=Burbank, California|date=April 23, 2009 |accessdate=July 27, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100407010117/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2009/04/23/demi-lovato-graduates-high-school/ |archivedate=April 7, 2010 }}</ref> In 2006, Lovato appeared on ''[[Prison Break]]'', and on ''[[Just Jordan]]'' the following year.<ref name=\"BioChannelBiography\"/>\n\n===2007\u20132008: Breakthrough with ''Camp Rock'' and ''Don't Forget''===\n[[File:Demi Lovato Crop.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Lovato on the [[South Bank]], [[London]] in September 2008]]''\nFrom 2007 to 2008, Lovato played Charlotte Adams on the [[Disney Channel]] short series ''[[As the Bell Rings (U.S. TV series)|As the Bell Rings]]''.<ref name=AboutDemi>{{cite web|title=About Demi Lovato|url=http://demilovatotour.com/html/about_demi_lovato.html|publisher=demilovatotour.com|accessdate=September 13, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104011501/http://demilovatotour.com/html/about_demi_lovato.html |archivedate=November 4, 2013}}</ref> Lovato auditioned for the channel's television film ''[[Camp Rock]]'' and series ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'' during 2007 and got both roles.<ref name=\"Victoria\">{{cite news|url=http://www.victoriaadvocate.com/news/2009/jun/22/bc-mus-demilovatoaa-_-entertainment/?entertainment&national-entertainment|title=Disney singing sensation Demi Lovato ready for new album, first tour as headliner|first=John J.|last=Moser|work=[[The Victoria Advocate]]|publisher=Victoria Advocate Publishing Co.|date=June 22, 2009|accessdate=March 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130818042131/http://www.victoriaadvocate.com/news/2009/jun/22/bc-mus-demilovatoaa-_-entertainment/?entertainment&national-entertainment|archivedate=August 18, 2013}}</ref> Lovato played the lead character, aspiring singer Mitchie Torres, in ''Camp Rock''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kidstvmovies.about.com/od/camprock/fr/camprockr.htm|title=Camp Rock (2008) \u2013 Movie Review for Parents|first=Carey|last=Bryson|website=[[About.com]]|publisher=[[IAC (company)|IAC]]|location=New York City|accessdate=March 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130421105530/http://kidstvmovies.about.com/od/camprock/fr/camprockr.htm|archivedate=April 21, 2013}}</ref> The film premiered on June 20, 2008, to 8.9&nbsp;million viewers.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2008/06/high-ratings-fo.html|title=High ratings for 'Camp Rock,' the Disney Channel's Jonas Brothers movie|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=June 21, 2008|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> [[Gillian Flynn]] of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' wrote that Lovato's acting skills were underwhelming and that she \"has the knee-jerk smile of someone who is often told she has a great smile\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20206296,00.html|title=Camp Rock (2008)|first=Gillian|last=Flynn|authorlink=Gillian Flynn|date=June 20, 2008|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref> [[Camp Rock (soundtrack)|The film's soundtrack]] was released three days earlier; however, the music was considered less current than that of ''[[High School Musical]]''.<ref name=\"Hinkley\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/camp-rock-rock-steady-disney-hit-article-1.293920|title='Camp Rock' is a rock-steady Disney hit|first=David|last=Hinkley|work=[[New York Daily News]]|date=June 18, 2008|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> It debuted at number three on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], with 188,000 units sold in its first week of release.<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Katey|last=Hasty|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1044979/coldplay-cruises-to-no-1-on-the-billboard-200|title=Coldplay Cruises To No. 1 On The Billboard 200|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=June 25, 2008|access-date=June 24, 2019}}</ref> Lovato sang four songs on the soundtrack, including \"[[We Rock (Camp Rock song)|We Rock]]\" and \"[[This Is Me (Demi Lovato song)|This Is Me]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0017LFKMO |title=Camp Rock: Original Television Soundtrack: Music|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> The latter, Lovato's debut single, debuted at number 11 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and later peaked at number nine, marking her first entry on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100|title=Top 100 Songs {{!}} Billboard Hot 100 Chart|website=Billboard|access-date=May 11, 2019}}</ref> That summer, Lovato signed with [[Hollywood Records]] and began her [[Demi Live! Warm Up Tour]] before the release of her debut studio album,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ovguide.com/demi-live!-warm-up-tour-9202a8c04000641f800000000879c65e|title=Demi Live! Warm Up Tour Video|publisher=OVGuide|accessdate=March 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022024108/http://www.ovguide.com/demi-live!-warm-up-tour-9202a8c04000641f800000000879c65e|archivedate=October 22, 2013}}</ref> and appeared on the [[Jonas Brothers]]' [[Burnin' Up Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zvents.com/essex_junction_vt/events/show/83554500-jonas-brothers-the-burning-up-tour-with-special-guest-demi-lovato |title=Jonas Brothers: The Burning Up Tour with special guest Demi Lovato |publisher=Zvents |accessdate=March 11, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103200933/http://www.zvents.com/essex_junction_vt/events/show/83554500-jonas-brothers-the-burning-up-tour-with-special-guest-demi-lovato |archivedate=November 3, 2013 }}</ref>\n\nLovato's debut studio album, ''[[Don't Forget]]'', was released on September 23, 2008, and was met with generally positive reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=1279002|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 Don't Forget|work=AbsolutePunk.net|accessdate=August 26, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120716221811/http://www.absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=1279002|archivedate=July 16, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"DigitalSpy\">{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/albumreviews/a154015/demi-lovato-dont-forget.html|title=Demi Lovato: 'Don't Forget'|date=April 20, 2009|last=Levine|first=Nick|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=April 26, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Allmusic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/here-we-go-again-r2278939/review|title=Here We Go Again \u2013 Demi Lovato|work=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|location=San Carlos, California|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|accessdate=October 9, 2011}}</ref> Michael Slezak of ''Entertainment Weekly'' said, \"Demi Lovato might satisfy her 'tween fans but she won't be winning any rockers over with ''Don't Forget''\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20226319,00.html|title=Don't Forget Review|first=Michael|last=Slezak|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=September 17, 2008|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> The album debuted at number two in the US, with first-week sales of 89,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/10/01/on-the-charts-demi-lovato-kings-of-leon-debut-high-metallica-rule/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081004053422/http://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/10/01/on-the-charts-demi-lovato-kings-of-leon-debut-high-metallica-rule/|title=On the Charts: Demi Lovato & Kings of Leon Debut High, Metallica Rule|first=Daniel|last=Kreps|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=October 1, 2008|archivedate=October 4, 2008|accessdate=March 10, 2013}}</ref> Ten of its songs were co-written with the Jonas Brothers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/15/music-jonas-dc-idUSN1541696620080615|title=Jonas Brothers thrilling tweens|first=Amy|last=Donahue|agency=[[Reuters]]|publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]]|location=London, England|date=June 25, 2008|accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref>\n\n''Don't Forget'' was certified gold by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for US sales of over 500,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Demi+Lovato&ti=don%27t+forget&lab=&genre=&format=&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section |title=Recording Industry Association of America|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|accessdate=March 18, 2017}}</ref> Its lead single, \"[[Get Back (Demi Lovato song)|Get Back]]\", was praised for its [[pop rock]] style and peaked at number 43 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, also selling over 560,000 copies in the United States.<ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/chartbeat/474115/ask-billboard-songs-two-good-not-to-be-no-1|title=Ask Billboard: Songs Two Good Not To Be No. 1|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 26, 2015|date=November 17, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/ae/music/cd_reviews/articles/2008/09/23/at_sweet_16_lovatos_ready_for_her_close_up/?camp=pm |title=At sweet 16, Lovato's ready for her close-up |newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]] |publisher=Boston Globe Media Partners, L.P.|location=Boston, Massachusetts |date=September 23, 2008 |accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"BillboardChartHistory\">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=demi lovato|chart=all}}|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 Chart History|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> The album's second single, \"[[La La Land (Demi Lovato song)|La La Land]]\", was cited for its strong rock elements<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/legacy/chartblog/2009/05/demi_lovato_la_la_land.shtml|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 'La La Land'|first=Fraser|last=McAlpine|publisher=[[BBC Music]]. [[BBC]]|date=May 31, 2009|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> and peaked at number 52 in the US,<ref name=\"BillboardChartHistory\"/> and cracked the top 40 in Ireland and the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2009&year=2009&week=18|title=Chart Track|publisher=[[Irish Singles Chart]]. GfK|accessdate=July 26, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/La%20La%20Land|title=The Official Charts Company \u2013 Demi Lovato \u2013 La La Land|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=July 26, 2011}}</ref> The music video for the song was directed by [[The Malloys|Brendan Malloy]] and Tim Wheeler.<ref name=\"Video\">{{cite AV media| people= Demi Lovato, Brendan Malloy, Tim Wheeler| title = Making the Video: La La Land|  medium = DVD| publisher =Don't Forget (Deluxe Edition)}}</ref>{{full citation needed|date=March 2019}} The third single and title track, \"[[Don't Forget (song)|Don't Forget]]\", peaked at number 41 in the US.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/demi-lovato|title=Demi Lovato Chart History|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=June 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132010: ''Sonny with a Chance'' and ''Here We Go Again''===\nIn 2009, Lovato recorded \"[[Send It On (Disney's Friends for Change song)|Send It On]]\", a [[charity record|charity single]] and the theme song for [[Disney's Friends for Change]], with costars the [[Jonas Brothers]], [[Miley Cyrus]] and [[Selena Gomez]].<ref name=\"pressrelease\">{{cite press release|url=https://thewaltdisneycompany.com/disney-news/press-releases/2009/08/send-it-anthem-worlds-biggest-teen-stars-miley-cyrus-jonas-0|title=\"Send It On\", an anthem by the world's biggest teen stars, Miley Cyrus, Jonas Brothers, Selena Gomez and Demi Lovato, for Disney's \"Friends For Change: Project Green\", will debut on Radio Disney, Disney Channel, disney.com and iTunes|date=August 6, 2009|publisher=The Walt Disney Company|accessdate=October 2, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?id=325770503&s=143441 |title=Send It On (feat. Demi Lovato, Jonas Brothers, Miley Cyrus & Selena Gomez) \u2013 Single |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] (US). [[Apple Inc.]] |date=August 11, 2009 |accessdate=August 20, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130722024414/https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?id=325770503&s=143441 |archivedate=July 22, 2013  }}</ref> All proceeds from the song were donated to environmental charities supported by the Disney Worldwide Conservation Fund.<ref name=\"pressrelease\" /> Lovato's Disney Channel sitcom ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'', in which she played Sonny Munroe, the newest cast member of the [[show-within-a-show]] ''So Random!'', premiered on February 8.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/sonny-with-a-chance-season-1/id303224140|title=Sonny With a Chance, Season 1|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple Inc|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> Lovato's acting ability was described by Robert Lloyd of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' as \"very good\", and he compared her favorably to ''[[Hannah Montana]]'' star Miley Cyrus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2009/feb/06/entertainment/et-sonny6 |title=Sonny With a Chance |first=Robert|last=Lloyd |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=February 6, 2009 |accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref> That June, she starred alongside Selena Gomez in the Disney Channel film ''[[Princess Protection Program]]'', in which Lovato portrayed Rosie Gonzalez / Princess Rosalinda. The film, the fourth highest-rated Disney Channel original movie, premiered to 8.5&nbsp;million viewers.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://blogs.mcall.com/tvwatchers/2009/07/jon-kate-divorce-episode-bet-jackson-tribute-draw-record-audiences.html |title=Jon & Kate divorce episode/ BET Jackson tribute draw record audiences |first=Kathy|last=Lauer-Williams |newspaper=[[The Morning Call]] |publisher=[[Tribune Company]] |location=[[Allentown, Pennsylvania]]|date=July 1, 2009|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[File:DemiLovatoSep10 4.jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato performing during the [[List of Jonas Brothers concert tours#Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert|Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert]] in September 2010]]\nLovato's second studio album, ''[[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato album)|Here We Go Again]]'', was released on July 21, 2009;<ref name=\"BioChannelBiography\"/> she described its acoustic style as similar to that of [[John Mayer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarslam.com/demi-lovato-on-second-album/|title=Demi Lovato on second album|author=Chelsea|date=January 28, 2009|publisher=Sugar Slam|accessdate=June 13, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090604140130/http://www.sugarslam.com/demi-lovato-on-second-album/|archive-date=June 4, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album received favorable reviews from critics who appreciated its enjoyable pop-rock elements, echoing reviews of ''Don't Forget''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/here-we-go-again/demi-lovato|title=Here We Go Again (2009): Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|location=Chicago, Illinois|accessdate=July 27, 2011}}</ref> Lovato's first number one album, it debuted atop the ''Billboard'' 200 with first-week sales of 108,000 copies, and was later certified Gold.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/267911/demi-lovato-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-but-michael-jackson-still-reigns|title=Demi Lovato Debuts At No. 1 On Billboard 200, But Michael Jackson Still Reigns|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=July 29, 2009|accessdate=March 10, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Gold & Platinum\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=May 11, 2019}}</ref> The album's lead single and title track, \"[[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato song)|Here We Go Again]]\", debuted at number 59 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, and managed to peak at number 15, becoming Lovato's highest peaking solo single at the time.<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=demi lovato|chart=all}}|title=Demi Lovato Album & Song Chart History \u2013 Hot 100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=October 9, 2011}}</ref> The song also peaked at number 68 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] and number 38 in New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=demi lovato|chart=Billboard Canadian Hot 100}} |title=Demi Lovato Album & Song Chart History \u2013 Canadian Hot 100 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=October 9, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query |archivedate=October 2, 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/here-we-go-again-mw0000822778|title=Here We Go Again \u2013 Demi Lovato|first=Stephen Thomas|last=Erlewine|website=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|location=San Carlos, California|date=July 21, 2009|accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref> \"Here We Go Again\" was additionally certified Platinum in the US.<ref name=\"Gold & Platinum\"/> The album's second and final single, \"[[Remember December]]\" failed to match the success of its predecessor, but peaked at number 80 on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. Lovato made her first 40-city national concert tour, Live in Concert, in support of ''Here We Go Again''.<ref name=\"Summer Tour 2009\">{{cite web|url=http://www.aeglive.com/news/view/10206|title=Demi Lovato Announces \"Summer Tour 2009\" North American Headline Tour|publisher=AEG Live|accessdate=January 1, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416183028/http://www.aeglive.com/news/view/10206|archive-date=April 16, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The tour, from June 21 to August 21, 2009,<ref name=\"LiveInConcert\">{{cite web|url=http://www.artistdirect.com/nad/news/article/0,,5289041,00.html|title=Demi Lovato Lines Up Lengthy Summer Tour|date=April 16, 2009|publisher=ArtistDirect|accessdate=October 5, 2013}}</ref> had [[David Archuleta]],<ref name=\"LiveInConcert\" /> [[KSM (band)|KSM]] and [[Jordan Pruitt]] as opening acts.<ref>{{cite web|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1609297/demi-lovato-to-tour-with-david-archuleta-this-summer/|title=Demi Lovato To Tour With David Archuleta This Summer|date=April 15, 2009|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|accessdate=October 5, 2013}}</ref> Lovato and Archuleta received the Choice Music Tour award at the [[2009 Teen Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/Winners-2009-Teen-Choice-Awards-3904879|title=Announcing the Winners of the 2009 Teen Choice Awards!|website=[[Buzz Sugar]]|date=August 9, 2009|accessdate=October 5, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Lovato and [[Joe Jonas]] recorded \"[[Make a Wave]]\" as the second charity single for Disney's Friends for Change.<ref name=\"iTunesMakeAWave\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/make-wave-feat.-joe-jonas/id361074253|title=Make a Wave (feat. Joe Jonas & Demi Lovato) \u2013 EP|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple Inc|date=March 15, 2010|accessdate=March 13, 2013}}</ref> In May of that year, Lovato guest-starred as Hayley May, a teenager with [[schizophrenia]], in the [[Grey's Anatomy (season 6)|sixth-season]] ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' episode, \"[[Shiny Happy People (Grey's Anatomy)|Shiny Happy People]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrolyrics.com/2010-demi-lovato-stars-in-greys-anatomy-news.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100522045923/http://www.metrolyrics.com/2010-demi-lovato-stars-in-greys-anatomy-news.html|title=Demi Lovato stars in Grey's Anatomy|website=[[MetroLyrics]]|date=May 14, 2010|archivedate=May 22, 2010|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref> Although critics praised her versatility, they were underwhelmed by her acting and felt that her appearance was designed primarily to attract viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/photos/53471/1/Demi-Lovato-Stars-In-Greys-Anatomy-Pictures|title=Demi Lovato Stars In Grey's Anatomy \u2013 Pictures|first=Helen|last=Sanders|website=Entertainment Wise|date=May 14, 2010|accessdate=June 2, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131106182729/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/photos/53471/1/Demi-Lovato-Stars-In-Greys-Anatomy-Pictures|archivedate= November 6, 2013}}</ref> Later that year, she headlined her first international tour, [[Demi Lovato: Live in Concert]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/03/21/demi-lovato-announces-south-american-tour-2010/ |title=Demi Lovato Announces South American Tour 2010 |website=[[Disney Dreaming]] |publisher=[[Walt Disney Company]]|location=Burbank, California|date=March 21, 2010 |accessdate=October 5, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131006170036/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/03/21/demi-lovato-announces-south-american-tour-2010/ |archivedate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/531920790|title=Demi's coming to South America!! |website=[[Myspace]]|publisher=Specific Media LLC|location=Beverly Hills, California|date=March 30, 2010|accessdate=March 13, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120327073542/http://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/531920790|archivedate=March 27, 2012}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> and joined the [[List of Jonas Brothers concert tours#Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert|Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert]] tour as a guest.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/533484912|title=Summer tour announcement|website=[[Myspace]]|publisher= Specific Media LLC|location=Beverly Hills, California|date=April 27, 2010 |accessdate=March 13, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120327073553/http://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/533484912|archivedate=March 27, 2012}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n\n''[[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam]]'', with Lovato reprising her role as Mitchie Torres, premiered on September 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1637866/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-premieres-september-3-on-disney-channel/|title='Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam' Premieres September 3 On Disney Channel|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|date=April 27, 2010|accessdate=May 14, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam Premier Had 8 Million Viewers |url=http://www.bsckids.com/2010/09/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-premier-had-8-million-viewers/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827173931/http://www.bsckids.com/2010/09/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-premier-had-8-million-viewers/|first=Sarah|last=Peel|website=BSC Kids|date=September 7, 2010|archivedate=August 27, 2011|accessdate=March 14, 2010}}</ref> Critics were ambivalent about the film's plot, and it has a 40-percent approval rating on [[Rotten Tomatoes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/camp-rock-2/|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (2010)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|location=Los Angeles, California|accessdate=March 13, 2013}}</ref> However, Lovato's performance was called \"dependably appealing\" by Jennifer Armstrong of ''Entertainment Weekly''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20415589,00.html|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam|first=Jennifer|last=Armstrong|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 25, 2010|accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref> The film premiered to eight million viewers, the number-one cable television movie of the year by the number of viewers.<ref name=\"CR2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.medialifemagazine.com/camp-rock-2-becomes-years-top-movie/|title='Camp Rock 2' becomes year's top movie|first=Toni|last=Fitzgerald|work=[[Media Life Magazine]]|publisher=Media Life Co.|location=Portland, Oregon|date=September 7, 2010|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> Its accompanying [[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] was released on August 10 with Lovato singing nine songs, including \"[[Can't Back Down (song)|Can't Back Down]]\" and \"[[Wouldn't Change a Thing (Camp Rock song)|Wouldn't Change a Thing]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/camp-rock-2-final-jam-soundtrack/id385086976|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (Soundtrack from the Motion Picture)|publisher=iTunes Store (U S). Apple Inc|date=August 10, 2010|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> The soundtrack debuted at number three on the ''Billboard'' 200, with first-week sales of 41,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oceanup.com/2010/08/18/camp-rock-2-soundtrack-41863-sold/|title=Camp Rock 2 Soundtrack 41,863 Sold|work=OceanUp|publisher=As If Productions|location=Los Angeles, California|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> ''[[The Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert]]'' was reworked to incorporate Lovato and the rest of the film's cast;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/04/27/jonas-brothers-2010-world-tour-camp-rock-2-tour/ |title=Jonas Brothers 2010 World Tour Camp Rock 2 Tour 20 of the show have been cancelled or moved |website=[[Disney Dreaming]]|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]] |location=Burbank, California|date=April 27, 2010 |accessdate=March 13, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130816182438/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/04/27/jonas-brothers-2010-world-tour-camp-rock-2-tour/ |archivedate=August 16, 2013 }}</ref> it began on August 7, two weeks later than planned.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/07/03/jonas-brothers-cancel-camp-rock-2-tour-dates-add-others/ |title=Jonas Brothers Cancel Camp Rock 2 Tour Dates, Add Others |website=[[Disney Dreaming]] |publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|location=Burbank, California|date=July 3, 2010 |accessdate=March 13, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120829033628/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/07/03/jonas-brothers-cancel-camp-rock-2-tour-dates-add-others/ |archivedate=August 29, 2012 }}</ref> The ''[[Sonny with a Chance (soundtrack)|Sonny with a Chance]]'' soundtrack was released on October 5; Lovato sang on four tracks, including \"[[Me, Myself and Time]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/hanging/id394754821?i=394754911|title=Sonny With a Chance (Soundtrack from the TV Series)|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple Inc|date=October 5, 2010|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> It debuted (and peaked) at number 163 on the ''Billboard'' 200, her lowest-selling soundtrack.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/sonny-with-a-chance-mw0002032615/awards|title=Sonny with a Chance \u2013 Original TV Soundtrack: Awards|website=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|location=San Carlos, California|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref> In November 2010, Lovato announced her departure from ''Sonny with a Chance'', putting her acting career on hiatus and ending the series;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/237137/demi-lovato-quitting-sonny-with-a-chance|title=Demi Lovato Quitting Sonny With a Chance|first=Josh|last=Grossberg|date=April 19, 2011|website=[[E!]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|location=New York City|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> she later said that she would return to acting when she felt confident doing so.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KFFkhGJ_RiY|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 Koko Pop UK|date=April 7, 2012|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref> Her departure led to the actual spin-off series ''[[So Random!]]'' with the ''Sonny'' cast, featuring sketches from the former show-within-a-show. The series was cancelled after one season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2011/04/19/demi-lovato-exits-sonny-with-a-chance/|title=Demi Lovato Exits Disney Series: 'I Don't Think It Would Be Healthy for My Recovery{{'-}}|date=April 19, 2011|work=[[TVLine]]|location=Los Angeles, California|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130310192437/http://tvline.com/2011/04/19/demi-lovato-exits-sonny-with-a-chance/|archivedate=March 10, 2013|url-status=dead|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===2011\u20132012: ''Unbroken'' and ''The X Factor''===\n[[File:Demi Lovato 8, 2012.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Lovato performing on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' in July 2012 as part of their Summer Concert Series]]\nLovato released her third studio album, ''[[Unbroken (Demi Lovato album)|Unbroken]]'', on September 20, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1667730/demi-lovato-new-album-september/|title=Demi Lovato To Release New Album September 20|author=James Dinh|publisher=MTV News. Viacom|date=July 22, 2011|accessdate=March 15, 2013}}</ref> Begun in July 2010, the album experimented with [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] and featured less pop rock than her first two albums.<ref name=\"Vena\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1644100/demi-lovato-wants-to-embrace-her-inner-soul-diva-on-next-album/|title=Demi Lovato Wants To Embrace Her 'Inner Soul' Diva On Next Album|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|date=July 21, 2010|work=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|accessdate=March 15, 2013}}</ref> Lyrically, ''Unbroken'' encompasses more mature themes as opposed to Lovato's previous work, with some songs focusing on Lovato's personal struggles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1670726/demi-lovato-unbroken-reviews/|title=Demi Lovato's Unbroken: Putting It Back Together|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|website=MTV News|language=en|access-date=June 24, 2019}}</ref> The album and its stylistic change received mixed reviews from critics, who praised Lovato's vocals and saw a growth in her musicianship due to the songs focusing on her struggles, but criticized the album's \"party songs\" and found the music to be more generic than her previous efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/unbroken-2010/demi-lovato/critic-reviews|title=Critic Reviews for Unbroken|publisher=Metacritic. CBS Interactive|accessdate=March 15, 2013}}</ref> ''Unbroken'' debuted at number four in the US, selling 97,000 copies in its first week of release; it was later certified Gold.<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/467230/tony-bennett-85-achieves-first-no-1-album-on-billboard-200 |title=Tony Bennett, 85, Achieves First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 |work=Billboard |first=Tony|last=Caulfield|date=September 28, 2011 |accessdate=May 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\n\"[[Skyscraper (song)|Skyscraper]]\", the lead single from ''Unbroken'', was released on July 12, and was noted for its messages of self-worth and confidence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/Demi-Lovato-Skyscraper.htm|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 \"Skyscraper\"|author=Bill Lamb|publisher=About.com. IAC|accessdate=June 2, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130505015245/http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/Demi-Lovato-Skyscraper.htm|archivedate=May 5, 2013}}</ref> It debuted at number ten in the US, selling 176,000 downloads during the first week of release, becoming Lovato's highest first week sales at the time.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/> The song also became Lovato's highest-peaked single since \"[[This Is Me (Camp Rock song)|This Is Me]]\" reached number nine in July 2008,<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/469163/lmfao-still-atop-hot-100-demi-lovato-debuts-in-top-10|title=LMFAO Still Atop Hot 100, Demi Lovato Debuts In Top 10|last=Trust|first=Gary|work=Billboard|date=July 20, 2011 |accessdate=July 20, 2011}}</ref> and it also debuted at number two on the [[Hot Digital Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/469172/blake-sheltons-river-runs-to-no-1-on-billboard-200|title=Blake Shelton's 'River' Runs to No. 1 on Billboard 200|date=July 20, 2011|last=Caulfield|first=Kevin|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 20, 2011}}</ref> \"Skyscraper\" received the Best Video With a Message award at the September [[2012 MTV Video Music Awards]], and the track was also certified Platinum by the RIAA and Silver by the [[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/ontv/vma/2012/best-video-with-a-message/|title=Demi Lovato nominated for Best Video With A Message at the 2012 VMA's.|publisher=MTV News. Viacom|date=July 31, 2012|accessdate=March 15, 2013}}</ref> The album's second and final single, \"[[Give Your Heart a Break]]\", was released on January 23, 2012, and later peaked on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number 16, making Lovato's fourth highest peaking song at the time.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=demi lovato|chart=all}} |title=Hot 100 Songs & New Music: 1 \u2013 10 Songs &#124; Billboard Music Charts |magazine=Billboard.com |accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> It peaked at number 12 on the US [[Adult Pop Songs|Adult Top 40]] chart and number one on the US [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Pop Songs]] chart. It also became the longest climb by a female artist to reach No. 1 in the [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Pop Songs]] chart history, until 2019, when [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]]'s feature on \"[[Eastside (song)|Eastside]]\" broke the record.<ref name=\"BillboardChartHistory\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8499744/benny-blanco-halsey-khalid-eastside-no-1-pop-songs|title=Benny Blanco, Halsey & Khalid Complete Record Rise to No. 1 on Pop Songs Chart With 'Eastside'|website=Billboard|access-date=March 24, 2019|date=February 25, 2019}}</ref> The song was certified triple Platinum in the US; {{as of|2014|October|lc=y}}, \"Give Your Heart a Break\" sold 2.1 million digital copies.<ref name=\"sales\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6281548/ask-billboard-baseball-hits-gwen-stefanis-delay-demi-lovatos?page=0%2C4|title=Ask Billboard: Baseball Hits, Gwen Stefani's Delay & Demi Lovato's Best-Selling Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 12, 2014 |accessdate=October 12, 2014 }}</ref> [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] has rated the song as Lovato's best, calling it \"timeless\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8238640/demi-lovato-best-songs-top-10|title=Demi Lovato's 10 Best Songs: Critic's Picks|website=Billboard|access-date=June 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn May, Lovato became a judge and mentor for the [[The X Factor (U.S. season 2)|second season]] of the [[The X Factor (U.S. TV series)|U.S. version]] of ''[[The X Factor]]'', with a reported salary of one million dollars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zap2it.com/blogs/demi_lovatos_x_factor_salary_cant_compare_to_britney_spears-2012-05|title=Demi Lovato's 'X Factor' salary can't compare to Britney Spears'|publisher=Zap2It|date=May 30, 2012|accessdate=March 7, 2013}}</ref> Joining [[Britney Spears]], [[Simon Cowell]], and [[L.A. Reid]],<ref name=\"JoinX-Factor\">{{cite web|last=Bricker|first=Tierney|title=It's Official! Demi Lovato Joins X Factor as Fourth Judge|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/315906/it-s-official-demi-lovato-joins-x-factor-as-fourth-judge|publisher=E! Online|date=May 13, 2012|accessdate=May 13, 2012}}</ref> it was speculated that she was chosen to attract a younger audience.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1684289/demi-lovato-x-factor-judge-miley-cyrus/|title=Demi Lovato, Miley Cyrus Rumored For 'X Factor' Judge Spot|author=Gil Kaufman|publisher=MTV News. Viacom|date=May 2, 2012|accessdate=May 16, 2012}}</ref> Mentoring the Young Adults category, her final act (CeCe Frey) finished sixth.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1698571/x-factor-cece-frey-elimination-reaction/|title=CeCe Frey 'Knew' She Wasn't Going To Win 'X Factor'|author=Chris Kim|publisher=MTV News. Viacom|date=December 7, 2012|accessdate=March 15, 2013}}</ref> At the Minnesota State Fair in August, Lovato announced that after a pre-show performance at the 2012 MTV Video Music Awards<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kovideo.net/demi-lovato-reveals-she-is-recording-fourth-album-soon-news-demi-lovato-6153.html |first=Irene|last=Test|title=Demi Lovato Reveals She is Recording Fourth Album Soon |work=Kovideo |publisher=Glam Entertainment |date=September 1, 2012 |accessdate=March 16, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130402182638/http://www.kovideo.net/demi-lovato-reveals-she-is-recording-fourth-album-soon-news-demi-lovato-6153.html |archivedate=April 2, 2013 }}</ref> she would release a single by December.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ashley E. |url=http://www.bsckids.com/2012/08/demi-lovato-to-release-new-single-by-december/ |title=Demi Lovato To Release New Single By December |publisher=Bsckids |date=August 31, 2012 |accessdate=March 16, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120905131521/http://www.bsckids.com/2012/08/demi-lovato-to-release-new-single-by-december/ |archivedate=September 5, 2012 }}</ref> On December 24, she released a video on her [[YouTube]] account of herself singing \"[[Angels Among Us]]\" dedicated to the victims of the [[Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r8TgMkbMPkc|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 Angels Among Us |publisher=YouTube|date=December 24, 2012}}</ref> In March, she was confirmed as returning for ''The X Factor''{{'}}s [[The X Factor (U.S. season 3)|third season]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/1554926/demi-lovato-returning-for-third-season-of-x-factor|title=Demi Lovato Returning for Third Season of 'X Factor'|work=Billboard|date=March 28, 2013|accessdate=March 29, 2013}}</ref> with her salary reportedly doubling.<ref>{{cite news|title=Demi Lovato Making More Money Than Paulina Rubio, Kelly Rowland In 'The X Factor'|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/05/22/demi-lovato-making-more-money-than-paulina-rubio-and-kelly-rowland-for-x-factor/|publisher=Fox News Latino. 21st Century Fox|accessdate=May 26, 2013|date=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615010806/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/05/22/demi-lovato-making-more-money-than-paulina-rubio-and-kelly-rowland-for-x-factor/|archive-date=June 15, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''Demi''===\n[[File:Demi Lovato 2, 2013.jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato at the Redlight Traffic's Inaugural Dignity Gala in October 2013]]\nLovato's fourth studio album, ''[[Demi (album)|Demi]]'' was released on May 14, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2013/4/1/demi-lovato-releasing-new-album-demi-on-may-14.html|title=Demi Lovato Releasing New Album \"Demi\" on May 14|work=ABC News Radio|author=Andrea Dresdale|date=April 1, 2013|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref> The album features influences of [[synthpop]] and [[bubblegum pop]] and was met with generally positive reviews from music critics.<ref name=\"metacritic1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/demi/demi-lovato |title=''Demi'' Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Corporation]] |location=Chicago, Illinois|accessdate=May 15, 2013}}</ref> Although Jon Carmichael of ''[[The New York Times]]'' found Lovato's transition fun, according to ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' it signified a less-mature image.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/14/arts/music/demi-lovato-and-talib-kweli-have-new-albums.html |title=New Albums by Demi Lovato and Talib Kweli |first=Jon|last=Carmichael |newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=May 13, 2013 |accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2013/05/07/demi-lovatos-new-album-demi-now-streaming-online-read-ews-review-here/|title=Demi Lovato's new album 'Demi' now streaming online|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=May 7, 2013|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> The album debuted at number three in the US, with first-week sales of 110,000 copies, the highest selling debut week of Lovato's discography.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1563130/vampire-weekend-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-chart|title=Vampire Weekend Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart|author=Keith Caulfield|work=Billboard|date=May 22, 2013|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> It was also successful internationally, charting in the top ten in New Zealand, Spain and the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/album/34b93/Demi-Lovato-Demi|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 Demi|publisher=Ultratop. Hung Medien|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> The album has been certified Gold in the US.<ref name=\"us_sales\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Demi+Lovato&ti=&lab=&genre=&format=Album&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section|title=American album certifications \u2013 Demi Lovato \u2013 Demi|date=July 11, 2016|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]|accessdate=March 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe lead single from ''Demi'', \"[[Heart Attack (Demi Lovato song)|Heart Attack]],\" was released on February 25, and debuted at number 12 in the US, with first-week sales of 215,000 copies, the highest first week sales of Lovato's discography.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1550739/baauers-harlem-shake-still-atop-hot-100-although-lead-shrinks|title=Baauer's 'Harlem Shake' Still Atop Hot 100, Although Lead Shrinks|author=Gary Trust|work=Billboard|date=March 6, 2013|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1555888/macklemore-ryan-lewis-top-hot-100-imagine-dragons-ariana-grande-hit-top-10|title=Macklemore & Ryan Lewis Top Hot 100; Imagine Dragons, Ariana Grande Hit Top 10|author=Gary Trust|work=Billboard|date=April 3, 2013|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> The song peaked at number 10 (Lovato's third showing in the US top ten),<ref name=\"BillboardChartHistory\" /> and was also successful in the UK, Australia, and Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/song/110bf5/Demi-Lovato-Heart-Attack|title=Demi Lovato \u2013 Heart Attack|publisher=[[Ultratop]]. Hung Medien|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> The second single, \"[[Made in the USA (song)|Made in the USA]]\" peaked at number 80 in the US.<ref name=\"sales\" /> The third and fourth singles from ''Demi'', \"[[Neon Lights (Demi Lovato song)|Neon Lights]]\" and \"[[Really Don't Care]]\", both peaked in the top forty of the US, and at number one in the country's [[Dance Club Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1823485/its-demi-lovatos-demiversary-new-single-new-lyric-video-and-performances |title=It's Demi Lovato's #Demiversary: New Single, New Lyric Video And Performances |website=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|date= |accessdate=August 3, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-09-06/dance-club-play-songs|title=Hot Dance Club Songs |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=September 6, 2014|accessdate=August 28, 2014}}</ref> They were also certified Platinum in the US.<ref name=\"riaa.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=June 1, 2019}}</ref> \n\nLovato later released a deluxe version of ''Demi'', which was to include seven new tracks, consisting of four live performances and three studio recordings.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nz.news.yahoo.com/a/-/latest/25441065/demi-lovato-announces-demi-deluxe |title=Demi Lovato announces Demi \u2013 Deluxe |publisher= |url-status=dead|archiveurl= https://archive.today/20141107021305/https://nz.news.yahoo.com/a/-/latest/25441065/demi-lovato-announces-demi-deluxe/|archivedate=November 7, 2014|date=November 6, 2014}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> One of these songs included a collaboration with [[Olly Murs]] on a song for his fourth studio album, entitled \"[[Up (Olly Murs song)|Up]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.directlyrics.com/preview-demi-lovato-olly-murs-up-30-second-snippet-news.html|title=Preview: Demi Lovato & Olly Murs \u2013 \"Up\" [30 Second Snippet]|work=Directlyrics}}</ref> Lovato contributed to [[The Mortal Instruments: City of Bones (soundtrack)|''The Mortal Instruments: City of Bones'' soundtrack album]] with \"Heart by Heart\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Guidry |first=Ken |title='The Mortal Instruments: City Of Bones' Soundtrack Features Jessie J, Demi Lovato, Owl City & More |url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/the-mortal-instruments-city-of-bones-soundtrack-features-jessie-j-demi-lovato-owl-city-more-20130702 |work=[[IndieWire]] |accessdate=August 11, 2013 |date=July 2, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130813083820/http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/the-mortal-instruments-city-of-bones-soundtrack-features-jessie-j-demi-lovato-owl-city-more-20130702 |archivedate=August 13, 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\nOn June 11, Lovato released an [[e-book]], ''Demi'', on [[iBooks]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2013/05/23/demi-lovato-ebook/|title=Buzz Bites (5/23/13): Demi Lovato Is Releasing An E-Book!|first=Althea|last=Legaspi|date=May 23, 2013|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|accessdate=May 26, 2013}}</ref> She planned to appear in at least six episodes of the [[Glee (season 5)|fifth season]] of ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'', but she only appeared in four. She played Dani, a struggling New York-based artist who befriends [[Rachel Berry]] ([[Lea Michele]]) and [[Santana Lopez]] ([[Naya Rivera]]) and interacts with fellow newcomer [[Adam Lambert]]'s character. Lovato debuted in the season's second episode, which aired on October 3, and made her final appearance in March 2014.<ref name=DemiGlee>{{cite web|last=Strecker|first=Erin|title=Demi Lovato headed to 'Glee'|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2013/08/22/demi-lovato-glee-phoebe-strole/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly|Inside TV]]|date=August 22, 2013|accessdate=August 22, 2013}}</ref> On November 19, she released a book, ''Staying Strong: 365 Days a Year'', which topped ''The New York Times'' bestseller list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/bookclub/news/a992770/demi-lovato-becomes-a-new-york-times-bestseller-with-book-staying-strong-365-days-a-year/ |title=Demi Lovato becomes a ''New York Times'' bestseller with book ''Staying Strong: 365 Days A Year''|website=Sugarscape |date=September 15, 2011 |accessdate=December 24, 2013}}</ref> She then agreed to write a [[memoir]], which has yet to be released.<ref name=StayingStrong>{{cite news|last=Deutsch|first=Lindsay|title=Demi Lovato is writing an inspirational book|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/books/2013/09/09/demi-lovato-book-deal/2787867/|newspaper=[[USA Today]]|publisher=[[Gannett Company]]|location=Mclean, Virginia|accessdate=September 9, 2013|date=September 9, 2013}}</ref> While in ''The X Factor'', her final act (Rion Paige) finished fifth.\n\nShe announced her ''[[The Neon Lights Tour|Neon Lights Tour]]'' (including a Canadian leg) on September 29, 2013,<ref>{{cite web|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|title=Demi Lovato Announces 2014 Tour with Little Mix, Cher Lloyd, Fifth Harmony|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5740663/demi-lovato-announces-2014-tour-with-little-mix-cher-lloyd-fifth|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=October 1, 2013|date=September 30, 2013}}</ref> which began February 9, 2014 and ended May 17.<ref name=\"NeonLightsTour\">{{cite web|last=Lovato|first=Demi|title=Neon Lights Tour|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=550289248377294|publisher=Facebook|accessdate=September 29, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"NeonBrazilMexico\">{{cite web|last=Lovato|first=Demi|title=The Neon Lights Tour comes to Brazil and Mexico|url=http://www.demilovato.com/the-neon-lights-tour-comes-to-brazil-and-mexico/|website=demilovato.com|date=October 14, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019090346/http://www.demilovato.com/the-neon-lights-tour-comes-to-brazil-and-mexico/|archivedate=October 19, 2013}}</ref> On October 21, she released her cover of \"[[Let It Go (Demi Lovato song)|Let It Go]]\" for the Disney film ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'', which was released in theaters on November 27. Lovato's cover was described as more \"radio friendly\" and \"pop\" as compared to the original by [[Idina Menzel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/12/04/disney-let-it-go-frozen-lawsuit-volar-youtube-cover-views/|title=Disney Sued Over Alleged \"Let It Go\" Song Theft, Millions Of YouTube Covers Could Be Affected|date=December 4, 2017|website=Tubefilter|language=en-US|access-date=June 1, 2019}}</ref> Lovato's cover appears in the movie's credits, and the song was promoted as the single for the [[Frozen (soundtrack)|film's soundtrack]].<ref name=\"DemiFrozen\">{{cite web|last=Rubin|first=Julia Lynn|title=Demi Lovato Releases New Song 'Let It Go' From Disney's 'Frozen' Soundtrack|url=http://www.hngn.com/articles/15461/20131021/demi-lovato-releases-new-song-let-it-go-from-disneys-frozen-soundtrack-listen.htm|website=HNGN|date=October 21, 2013}}</ref> The song peaked in the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number 38, spending 20 weeks on the chart. It was certified double Platinum by the RIAA.<ref name=\"riaa.com\"/> On May 18, 2014, \"[[Somebody to You]]\" featuring Lovato was released as the fourth single from [[The Vamps (British band)|The Vamps]]' debut album, ''[[Meet the Vamps]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/somebody-to-you-feat.-demi/id880517513|title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 Somebody to You (feat. Demi Lovato) by The Vamps|publisher=itunes.apple.com}}</ref> On May 29, she announced her fourth concert tour (and first world tour, covering 25 cities), the [[Demi World Tour]], and its first North American dates.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/546419/demi-lovato-announces-first-world-tour-dates|website=[[E!]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|location=New York City|date=May 29, 2014|accessdate=May 29, 2014|first=Zach|last=Johnson|title=Demi Lovato Announces First World Tour Dates!}}</ref> In November 2014, Lovato opened the UK shows on [[Enrique Iglesias]]' [[Sex and Love|Sex and Love Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a575916/enrique-iglesias-announces-uk-tour-with-demi-lovato.html |title=Enrique Iglesias announces UK tour with Demi Lovato \u2013 Music News |website=[[Digital Spy]]|date=June 6, 2014 |accessdate=August 3, 2014}}</ref> She also worked with her longtime friend [[Nick Jonas]] on a song for [[Nick Jonas (album)|his self-titled album]] called \"Avalanche,\" released November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7569396/nick-jonas-demi-lovato-avalanche-listen-duet|title=Nick Jonas And Demi Lovato's \"Avalanche\": Listen To Their Gorgeous Duet \u2013 Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on Idolator.com|work=Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on Idolator.com|date=November 6, 2014}}</ref> Lovato was featured on \"[[Up (Olly Murs song)|Up]]\", the second single from [[Olly Murs]]' fourth studio album, ''[[Never Been Better]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a612094/listen-to-olly-murs-and-demi-lovatos-new-single-up.html|title=Listen to Olly Murs and Demi Lovato's new single 'Up'|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=November 24, 2014|date=November 24, 2014|first=Finbow|last=Katy}}</ref>\n\nLovato announced her skincare line called ''Devonne by Demi'' to be available in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2014/09/03/demi-lovato-devonne-skincare-line/ |title=Demi Lovato on Her New Skincare Line: 'If You Use Products That Work, You'll Find Inner Confidence' |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|accessdate=September 3, 2014 |first=Ana |last=Calderone |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904000701/http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2014/09/03/demi-lovato-devonne-skincare-line/ |archivedate=September 4, 2014 |df= }}</ref> She released a music video for her song \"[[Nightingale (Demi Lovato song)|Nightingale]]\" on December 24, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=De Wilde|first1=Karen|title=Demi Lovato releases 'Nightingale' video showing Wilmer Valderrama|url=http://www.axs.com/news/demi-lovato-releases-nightingale-video-showing-wilmer-valderrama-34574|website=[[AXS (ticket merchant)|AXS]]|accessdate=April 5, 2015|date=December 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===2015\u20132016: ''Confident''===\n[[File:Demi Lovato, Future Now 2016 (Cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato performing during the [[Future Now Tour]] in September 2016]]\nLovato's fifth album, ''[[Confident (album)|Confident]]'', was released on October 16, 2015,<ref>{{cite news|title=Demi Lovato's fifth studio album 'Confident' due out Oct. 16|url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Music/2015/08/27/Demi-Lovatos-fifth-studio-album-Confident-due-out-Oct-16/6001440705839/|publisher=United Press International|accessdate=August 27, 2015|last1=Butler |first1=Karen |date=August 26, 2015}}</ref> and received generally positive reviews from music critics.<ref name=\"metacritic.com\">{{cite web|title=Reviews for Confident by Demi Lovato|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/confident/demi-lovato|website=Metacritic|accessdate=October 16, 2015}}</ref> The album debuted at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 with first-week sales of 98,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6738540/pentatonix-first-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart|title=Pentatonix Scores First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart|work=Billboard|date=October 26, 2015|accessdate=October 26, 2015|last1=Caulfield |first1= Keith}}</ref> During the album's production, Lovato commented: \"I've already started recording for my new album, and I have plans to record during the tour. The sound just evolves into everything that I've been and everything that I want to become.\"<ref name=\"Lovato Exit\">{{cite web|title=Demi Lovato Leaving 'X Factor'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5840366/demi-lovato-leaving-x-factor|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 19, 2013|last1=Lewis |first1=Hillary |last2=Willis |first2=Cortney |date=December 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Legaspi|first=Althea|title=Buzz Bites: Demi Lovato Has Begun Recording Her Fifth Studio Album|url= http://www.mtv.com/news/2306588/demi-lovato-fifth-album-details/|date=February 10, 2014|accessdate=April 5, 2014}}</ref> She further stated, \"I've never been so sure of myself as an artist when it comes down to confidence, but not only personal things, but exactly what I want my sound to be and what I know I'm capable of and this album will give me the opportunity to show people what I can really do.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Williott|first=Carl|title=Demi Lovato Is Already Working On Album #5|url=http://www.idolator.com/7505121/demi-lovato-tour-fifth-album|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|publisher=[[Spin Media]]|location=San Francisco, California|date=February 10, 2014|accessdate=April 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2019, the album was certified platinum by the RIAA, and has sold one million copies in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/chartdlovato/status/1220114014799310849?s=20|title={{!}} Demi's new certifieds in the United States: Sorry Not Sorry \u2014 5x Platinum Confident \u2014 2x Platinum Tell Me You Love Me \u2014 2x Platinum Stone Cold \u2014 Platinum Confident (Album) \u2014 Platinumpic.twitter.com/Xr1jFZYpYC|last=Charts|first=Demi Lovato|date=January 22, 2020|website=@chartdlovato|language=en|access-date=January 23, 2020}}</ref> In May 2015, ''Billboard'' revealed Lovato was in the process of starting an \"artist-centric\" new record label, [[Safehouse Records]], of which she will be co-founder and co-owner. The label will be a partnership between her, Nick Jonas, and Lovato's manager Phil McIntyre, and will form part of a new collaborative arrangement with record label [[Island Records|Island]].<ref name=island2015>{{cite web|url=http://www.islandrecords.com/artists/demi-lovato/ |title=Demi Lovato on Island Records Website |publisher=Island |accessdate=December 5, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160929182014/http://www.islandrecords.com/artists/demi-lovato/ |archivedate=September 29, 2016  }}</ref> ''Confident'' was released through the new venture deal. This will be Lovato's second multi-label venture of her career; she was formerly part of Jonas Records, a UMG/Hollywood/Jonas Brothers partnership, which is now defunct.<ref name=\"Safehouse Records (Billboard)\">{{cite news|last1=Halperin |first1=Shirley |title=Demi Lovato, Nick Jonas, Manager Phil McIntyre Launch Joint Venture with Island Records (Exclusive) |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6576003/demi-lovato-nick-jonas-manager-phil-mcintyre-launch-joint-venture-with |accessdate=May 26, 2015 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=May 26, 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528214542/http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6576003/demi-lovato-nick-jonas-manager-phil-mcintyre-launch-joint-venture-with |archivedate=May 28, 2015  |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\nLovato released the lead single from ''Confident'' titled \"[[Cool for the Summer]]\" on July 1, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Garibaldi|first1=Christina|title=YES! Demi Lovato Just Announced Her New Single 'Cool For The Summer'|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2196416/demi-lovato-cool-for-the-summer-single/|accessdate=June 25, 2015|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|date=June 25, 2015}}</ref> The song attracted attention for its [[bi-curious]] theme<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/07/demi-lovatos-cool-for-the-summer-is-the-anti-i-kissed-a-girl/398426/|title=Demi Lovato's 'Cool for the Summer': The Next Great Gay Anthem?|last=Kornhaber|first=Spencer|date=July 14, 2015|magazine=[[The Atlantic]]|publisher=[[Emerson Collective]]|location=Boston, Massachusetts|language=en-US|access-date=May 11, 2019}}</ref> and was a commercial success, peaking at number eleven on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and being certified double platinum in the U.S.<ref name=\"Gold & Platinum\"/><ref>{{cite web|first=Gordon|last=Murray|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6685062/demi-lovato-cool-for-summer-dance-club-songs-chart|title=Demi Lovato's 'Cool for the Summer' Is Fastest No. 1 on Dance Club Songs in Two Years|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=September 1, 2015|access-date=May 11, 2019}}</ref> On September 18, 2015, the title track \"[[Confident (Demi Lovato song)|Confident]]\" was released as the album's second single and peaked at number 21 on the Hot 100.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Maslow|first1=Nick|title=Demi Lovato Takes Control in Her New Song 'Confident': 'You Can't Make Me Behave'|url=https://people.com/celebrity/demi-lovato-releases-new-single-confident/|accessdate=September 20, 2015|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 18, 2015}}</ref> On October 17, 2015, she performed a \"Cool for the Summer\" and \"Confident\" medley, as well as \"[[Stone Cold (Demi Lovato song)|Stone Cold]]\" melody on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' during the series' [[Saturday Night Live (season 41)|forty-first season]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Lewittes|first=Michael|title=Demi Lovato Performs \"Cool For The Summer\" And \"Confident\" Medley On 'SNL' \u2013 WATCH VIDEO|url=http://www.gossipcop.com/demi-lovato-snl-cool-for-the-summer-confident-video-saturday-night-live-watch-performance/|accessdate=October 18, 2015|work=[[Gossip Cop]]|date=October 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kreps|first1=Daniel|title=See Demi Lovato's Confident 'SNL' Performances|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/news/see-demi-lovatos-confident-snl-performances-20151018|accessdate=October 19, 2015|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=October 18, 2015}}</ref> Lovato was also featured on the re-release of \"[[Irresistible (Fall Out Boy song)|Irresistible]]\", the fourth single from [[Fall Out Boy]]'s sixth studio album ''[[American Beauty/American Psycho]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/@falloutboy/fall-out-boy-are-smack-in-the-middle-of-leaving-the-hoth-system-in-empire-strikes-back-a6ebbdb49021|title=Fall Out Boy are smack in the middle of leaving the hoth system in empire strikes back\u2026|author=Fall Out Boy|work=[[Medium (website)|Medium]]|publisher=A Medium Corporation|location=New York City|date=October 12, 2015|accessdate=October 14, 2015}}</ref> The same month, she signed with the major modeling agency, [[Wilhelmina Models]].<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Demi Lovato Just Signed With a Major Modeling Agency|url= http://www.teenvogue.com/story/demi-lovato-signed-wilhelmina-major-modeling-agency|magazine=[[Teen Vogue]]|publisher=[[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]|location=New York City|accessdate=October 16, 2015|last1=Lewis |first1=Casey|date=October 16, 2015}}</ref> Lovato released the music video for her R&B-infused song \"[[Waitin for You]]\" featuring American rapper [[Sirah (rapper)|Sirah]] on October 22, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6738435/demi-lovato-tough-waitin-for-you-confident-video|title=Demi Lovato Gets Tough in 'Waitin for You' Video: Watch|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 23, 2015|accessdate=December 24, 2015|last=Stutz|first=Colin}}</ref> On October 26, 2015, Lovato and [[Nick Jonas]] announced that they would tour together on the [[Future Now Tour]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Strecker|first=Eric|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6738561/nick-jonas-demi-lovato-joint-tour|title=Nick Jonas & Demi Lovato Announce Joint Future Now Tour|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=November 4, 2015|date=October 26, 2015}}</ref> She was honored with the first-ever Rulebreaker Award on December 11, 2015 at the 2015 [[Billboard Women in Music|''Billboard'' Women in Music]] event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/women-in-music/6746374/demi-lovato-billboards-rulebreaker-women-in-music|title=Demi Lovato to Receive Billboard's Inaugural 'Rulebreaker' Award; Will Perform at Women in Music|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 23, 2015|date=November 2, 2015}}</ref> On March 21, 2016, \"Stone Cold\" was serviced as the third and final single from ''Confident''.<ref name=\"stonecold\">Sources regarding the contemporary hit radio release of \"Stone Cold\":\n*{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406152143/https://twitter.com/gthot20/status/710156449930993664|archive-date=April 6, 2016|url=https://twitter.com/gthot20/status/710156449930993664|title=.@ddlovato's \"Stone Cold\" goes to mainstream & adult top 40 radio Monday (March 21) ...|last=Trust|first=Gary|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=March 16, 2016|accessdate=April 6, 2016}}<!--Please do not remove, because Gary Trust is Billboard's associate director of charts/radio and editor of Billboard's Chart Beat column.-->\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.republicplaybook.com/track/demi-lovato-stone-cold/|title=Demi Lovato \"Stone Cold\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322112204/http://www.republicplaybook.com/track/demi-lovato-stone-cold/|archive-date=March 22, 2016|accessdate=March 22, 2016|work=[[Republic Records|Republic Playbook]]|publisher=[[Republic Records]]}}</ref> On July 1, 2016, Lovato released a new single titled \"[[Body Say]]\" to promote her tour.<ref name=\"bodysay\">{{cite news|last1=Iasimone|first1=Ashley|title=Demi Lovato Releases Steamy New Song 'Body Say'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7424023/demi-lovato-body-say-released-listen|accessdate=July 12, 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=July 2, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u20132018: ''Tell Me You Love Me''===\n[[File:Demi Lovato 8 (41898569045).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Lovato performing at the [[Tell Me You Love Me World Tour]] in June 2018]]\nIn February 2017, Lovato executive-produced a documentary, ''Beyond Silence'', which follows three individuals and their experiences with [[Mental disorder|mental illnesses]] including [[bipolar disorder]], [[schizophrenia]], [[Major depressive disorder|depression]], and [[Anxiety disorder|anxiety]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/demi-lovato-executive-produces-beyond-silence-mental-health-documentary-1201994230/|last1=Ahern|first1=Sarah|title=Demi Lovato on Her New Documentary: Mental Health Is 'Just as Important as Physical Health'|accessdate=March 1, 2017|date=February 22, 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> Lovato featured in [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]' song \"[[No Promises (Cheat Codes song)|No Promises]]\", released in March 2017,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Malone|first1=Dolph|title=Cheat Codes & Demi Lovato's \"No Promises\" Heading To Pop Radio|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2017/03/30/cheat-codes-demi-lovatos-no-promises-heading-pop-radio/|website=Headline Planet|accessdate=March 31, 2017|date=March 30, 2017}}</ref> and [[Jax Jones]]'s \"[[Instruction (song)|Instruction]]\" along with Stefflon Don, released in June 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Jax Jones Has Released A Snippet Of His Demi Lovato Collab & It Has Mad Carnival Vibes|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/demi-lovato/news/jax-jones-instruction/|work=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]]|date=June 14, 2017|access-date=June 14, 2016}}</ref> In 2017, Lovato was included in ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'''s annual list of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/4747191/time-100-john-legend-demi-lovato-gala/|title=TIME 100: John Legend and Demi Lovato to Perform at Gala|first=Mahita|last=Gajanan|accessdate=April 20, 2017|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/4745798/time-100-2017-full-list/|title=TIME 100: How the 2017 List of Influential People Was Chosen|first=Nancy|last=Gibbs|date=April 20, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]}}</ref> On May 8, 2017, she announced a collaboration with sportswear line [[Fabletics]] to support the [[United Nations]]' initiative, Girl Up.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lifestyle/7785106/demi-lovato-kate-hudson-fabletics-line-girl-up|title=Demi Lovato Teams Up With Kate Hudson's Fabletics Line to Support Girl Up|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Saunders|first=Nicole|date=May 8, 2017|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, Lovato released \"[[Sorry Not Sorry (Demi Lovato song)|Sorry Not Sorry]]\" as the first single from her sixth album,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3024567/demi-lovato-sorry-not-sorry/|title=Demi Lovato to Release New Single 'Sorry Not Sorry' July 11|publisher=MTV News|accessdate=September 22, 2017|date=July 11, 2017|first=Deepa|last=Lakshmin}}</ref> which became her highest charting song in New Zealand and the United States at number 6<ref name=\"NZ\">{{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Demi+Lovato|title=Discography Demi Lovato|publisher=New Zealand Charts|accessdate=October 30, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8015110/post-malone-rockstar-21-savage-hot-100-camila-cabello-havana-ed-sheeran-perfect|title=Post Malone & 21 Savage Lead Hot 100, Camila Cabello & Ed Sheeran Hit Top 10|journal=Billboard|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=October 30, 2017|accessdate=October 30, 2017}}</ref> as well as Australia at number 8.<ref>{{cite web|title=Taylor Swift holds #1 for second week|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2017/taylor-swift-holds-1-for-second-week|publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association|date=September 9, 2017|accessdate=October 7, 2017}}</ref> It also became her highest selling song in the US for its 5x Platinum certification by RIAA.<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1220114014799310849?s=20|title={{!}} Demi's new certifieds in the United States: Sorry Not Sorry \u2014 5x Platinum Confident \u2014 2x Platinum Tell Me You Love Me \u2014 2x Platinum Stone Cold \u2014 Platinum Confident (Album) \u2014 Platinumpic.twitter.com/Xr1jFZYpYC|author=Demi Lovato Charts|user=chartdlovato|date=January 22, 2020|website=@chartdlovato|language=en|access-date=January 23, 2020}}</ref> The album, titled ''[[Tell Me You Love Me (album)|Tell Me You Love Me]]'', was released on September 29 and opened at number three on the US ''Billboard'' 200 with first-week sales of 78,000 0 copies.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/demi-lovato-announces-new-album-tell-me-you-love-me-w499316|title=Demi Lovato Announces New Album 'Tell Me You Love Me'|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=August 24, 2017}}</ref><ref name=BBdebut>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7990429/shania-twain-now-debuts-no-1-billboard-200-albums-chart|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Shania Twain's 'Now' Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|journal=Billboard|date=October 8, 2017|accessdate=October 8, 2017}}</ref> It received positive reviews from music critics and became Lovato's first album to be certified Platinum in the US.<ref name=\"metacritic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/tell-me-you-love-me/demi-lovato|title= Demi Lovato \u2013 Tell Me You Love Me|website=[[Metacritic]]|date=September 29, 2017|accessdate=October 2, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://celebmix.com/demi-lovato-goes-platinum-with-tell-me-you-love-me/|title=Demi Lovato goes platinum with Tell Me You Love Me|date=April 8, 2018|website=CelebMix|language=en-GB|access-date=May 11, 2019}}</ref> On October 17, Lovato released ''[[Demi Lovato: Simply Complicated]]'' on [[YouTube]], a documentary focusing on her life, career, and personal struggles.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7980778/demi-lovato-simply-complicated-documentary-release-date|title=Demi Lovato Announces 'Simply Complicated' Documentary Release Date|first=Tatiana|last=Tenreyro|date=September 26, 2017|accessdate=October 17, 2017|magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref name=\"Documentary2017\" /> It was nominated for \"Best Music Documentary\" at the [[2018 MTV Movie & TV Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-2018-nominees-black-panther-stranger-things-1202381577/|title=MTV Movie & TV Awards: 'Black Panther', 'Stranger Things' Lead Pack In Nominations|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|date=May 3, 2018|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|language=en|access-date=May 11, 2019}}</ref> In October 2017, Lovato announced tour dates for the North American leg of her [[Tell Me You Love Me World Tour]], with special guests [[DJ Khaled]] and [[Kehlani]]. She confirmed European and South American legs of the tour in the following months, and the tour commenced in February 2018.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Blistein|first=Jon|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/demi-lovato-plots-2018-tour-with-dj-khaled-w510328|title=Demi Lovato Plots 2018 Tour With DJ Khaled|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=October 26, 2017|accessdate=October 26, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://popcrush.com/demi-lovato-tell-me-you-love-me-tour/|title=Demi Lovato's 'Tell Me You Love Me' Tour: Photos + Set List|website=[[PopCrush]]|date=February 27, 2018|accessdate=February 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017, Lovato released a song titled \"[[\u00c9chame la Culpa]]\" with [[Luis Fonsi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/demi-lovato-and-luis-fonsi-drop-fiery-music-video-their-spanish-song-echame-la-culpa-watch-91243|title=Demi Lovato and Luis Fonsi Drop the Fiery Music Video For Their Spanish Song 'Echame La Culpa' \u2013 Watch!|website=[[Entertainment Tonight|Entertainment Tonight Online]]|publisher=[[CBS Corporation]]|location=Chicago, Illinois}}</ref> Lovato performed at the [[March for Our Lives]] anti-gun violence rally in Washington, D.C. on March 24, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/demi-lovato-apos-performance-skyscraper-200620381.html|title=Demi Lovato's performance of \"Skyscraper\" at March for Our Lives will send actual chills through your body|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|date=March 25, 2018|accessdate=May 7, 2018|first=Mary Kate|last=McGrath}}</ref> In May, [[Christina Aguilera]] released a track from her album ''[[Liberation (Christina Aguilera album)|Liberation]]'' titled \"[[Fall in Line]]\" featuring Lovato,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/christina-aguilera-and-demi-lovato-release-their-much-anticipated-collaboration-fall-in-line__22928/|title=Christina Aguilera and Demi Lovato release their much-anticipated collaboration Fall In Line|publisher=Official Charts Company|last=White|first=Jack|date=May 16, 2018|accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref> and she was also featured on [[Clean Bandit]]'s song \"[[Solo (Clean Bandit song)|Solo]]\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Wass|first=Mike|title=Demi Lovato Lends Her Voice To Clean Bandit's Next Single, \"Solo\"|url=https://www.idolator.com/7679512/demi-lovato-clean-bandit-new-single-solo|accessdate=May 18, 2018|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|location=San Francisco, California|date=May 10, 2018}}</ref> The latter became Lovato's first number-one song in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|last=Myers |first=Justin|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/clean-bandit-and-demi-lovato-take-solo-to-number-1-we-cant-believe-it-__23225/|title=Clean Bandit and Demi Lovato take Solo to Number 1: \"We can't believe it!\"|publisher=Official Charts Company|date= June 22, 2018|accessdate= June 22, 2018}}</ref> On June 21, Lovato released a new single titled \"[[Sober (Demi Lovato song)|Sober]]\" which she referred to as \"my truth\" and discusses struggles with addiction and sobriety.<ref>{{cite news |title=Demi Lovato sings about addiction struggles on 'Sober' |url=http://www.thenewstribune.com/entertainment/celebrities/article213598949.html |newspaper=[[The News Tribune]] |accessdate=June 23, 2018 |date=June 21, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623222023/http://www.thenewstribune.com/entertainment/celebrities/article213598949.html |archive-date=June 23, 2018 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: Return to acting and seventh studio album===\nOn May 11, 2019, via an Instagram post, Lovato revealed that she had signed with a new manager, [[Scooter Braun]].<ref name=\"variety.com\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/demi-lovato-signs-scooter-braun-manager-1203212073/|title=Demi Lovato Signs With Scooter Braun for Management|date=May 12, 2019|website=Variety|access-date=May 13, 2019}}</ref> She shared that she \"couldn't be happier, inspired and excited to begin this next chapter\".<ref name=\"variety.com\" /> Throughout the year, Lovato teased fans on social media with hints of new music and revealed in August that a new album was on the way.<ref name=\"etonline.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/demi-lovato-drops-another-hint-about-her-upcoming-album-130889/|title=Demi Lovato Drops Another Hint About Her Upcoming Album|last=Gawley|first=Paige|date=August 21, 2019|website=[[Entertainment Tonight|Entertainment Tonight Online]]|publisher=[[CBS Corporation]]|location=Chicago, Illinois|access-date=September 1, 2019}}</ref> In August 2019, it was revealed that Lovato had joined the cast of ''[[Eurovision (film)|Eurovision]]'', a [[Netflix]] original movie, directed by [[David Dobkin (director)|David Dobkin]], based on the song competition [[Eurovision Song Contest|of the same name]]. Lovato is set to star alongside [[Will Ferrell]] and [[Rachel McAdams]].<ref name=\"Billboard Eurovision\">{{cite magazine|first=Ashley|last=Iasimone|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/news/movies/8527879/demi-lovato-eurovision-will-ferrell-cast-announcement/|title=Will Ferrell Welcomes Demi Lovato to 'Eurovision' Cast|date=August 20, 2019|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=September 1, 2019}}</ref> This marks Lovato's first acting role since guest starring in ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' in 2013. Later in the month, after teasing that she had been working on a new project, Lovato revealed via an Instagram post that she would be making her return to television with a guest role in the final season of [[NBC]] sitcom ''[[Will & Grace]]''.<ref name=\"eonline.com\">{{cite web|first=Chris|last=Harnick|url=https://www.eonline.com/uk/news/1068220/demi-lovato-joins-will-and-grace-s-final-season/|title=Demi Lovato Joins Will and Grace's Final Season|date=August 27, 2019|website=[[E! News]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|access-date=September 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, it was revealed that Lovato would make her return to music later that month with a performance of her comeback song \"[[Anyone (Demi Lovato song)|Anyone]]\" at the [[62nd Annual Grammy Awards]]. The song was released onto iTunes immediately following the performance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1116308/demi-lovato-releases-heartbreaking-song-anyone-after-2020-grammys-performance|title=Demi Lovato Releases Heartbreaking Song Anyone After 2020 Grammys|date=January 27, 2020|website=E! Online|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-03-16}}</ref> It marked Lovato's first musical appearance since her hiatus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5772107/demi-lovato-grammys/|title=Demi Lovato Brought the Audience to Its Feet In Her Grammys Return|last=Bruner|first=Raisa|date=January 27, 2020|website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|access-date=January 27, 2020}}</ref> On February 1, 2020, Lovato made a surprise with [[Dan + Shay]] by performing their song \"[[Speechless (Dan + Shay song)|Speechless]]\" on the ''[[Bud Light]] Super Bowl Music Fest''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc14news.com/2020/02/02/demi-lovato-joins-dan-shay-onstage-bud-light-super-bowl-music-fest-before-singing-at-the-big-game/amp/|title=Demi Lovato joins Dan + Shay onstage Bud Light Super Bowl Music Fest before singing at the big game|work=ABC 14 News|date=February 2, 2020|accessdate=February 2, 2020}}</ref> The following night, Lovato performed [[The Star-Spangled Banner]] at [[Super Bowl LIV]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2020/02/02/demi-lovato-super-bowl-liv-national-anthem-video-chiefs-49ers|title=Watch: Demi Lovato Sings National Anthem at Super Bowl LIV|last=Swinton|first=Elizabeth|date=February 2, 2020|website=[[Sports Illustrated]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=February 2, 2020}}</ref> A few days later, Lovato revealed that she would host a talk show, \"Pillow Talk With Demi Lovato\", to air on the new video streaming platform [[Quibi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/quibi-sets-demi-lovato-talk-show-pillow-talk-with-demi-lovato/|title=Quibi Sets Demi Lovato Talk Show 'Pillow Talk With Demi Lovato'|date=February 6, 2020|website=TheWrap|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref> On March 6, 2020, she released a new single titled \"[[I Love Me (song)|I Love Me]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/06/entertainment/demi-lovato-i-love-me-music-video/index.html|title=Demi Lovato drops new single and music video for 'I Love Me'|first=Chloe |last=Melas|publisher=CNN|date=March 6, 2020|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\n===Influences===\n{{multiple image\n| footer = [[Christina Aguilera]] (''left'') and [[Kelly Clarkson]] (''right'') both heavily influenced Lovato.\n| image1 =Christina Aguilera Sanremo.jpg\n| width1 = 144\n| alt1 = Christina Aguilera Performing\n| image2 =Kelly Clarkson 57th Presidential Inauguration-cropped.jpg\n| width2 = 153\n| alt2 = Kelly Clarkson Standing \n| align = right}}\n\nLovato has listed [[Christina Aguilera]] and [[Kelly Clarkson]] as her biggest influences.<ref name=\"influences\">{{cite web|title=Demi Talks About Her Influences|url=http://www.bopandtigerbeat.com/2011/09/demi-talks-about-her-influences/|work=[[Tiger Beat]]|accessdate=March 16, 2013|date=September 8, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921054808/http://www.bopandtigerbeat.com/2011/09/demi-talks-about-her-influences/|archive-date=September 21, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Her other influences include [[Britney Spears]],<ref name=younginf>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.younghollywood.com/scene/she-did-it-again-britney-spears-lands-back-on-top.html |title=SHE DID IT AGAIN: BRITNEY SPEARS LANDS BACK ON TOP |last=Boyce |first=Shannon |date=September 1, 2011 |accessdate=January 7, 2012 |website=[[Young Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Fremantle Media]]|location=Los Angeles, California|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020044704/https://www.younghollywood.com/scene/she-did-it-again-britney-spears-lands-back-on-top.html |archivedate=October 20, 2012  }}</ref> [[Rihanna]], [[Keri Hilson]],<ref name=\"Demi Lovato influence\">{{cite web|first=Marcell|last=Minaya|title=Lovato 'inspired by Rihanna R&B sound'|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a257783/lovato-inspired-by-rihanna-rb-sound.html|website=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=June 15, 2013|date=August 7, 2010}}</ref> [[Jennifer Lopez]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Demi Lovato inspired by Jennifer Lopez|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/demi-lovato-inspired-by-jennifer-lopez/|website=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=September 21, 2015|date=January 29, 2017}}</ref> [[Aretha Franklin]], [[Gladys Knight]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[Whitney Houston]], [[Alexz Johnson]],<ref name=\"Demi Lovato youth influences\">{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=cTW9Z7VKtQU|title=Demi Lovato talks about Alexz Johnson|date=October 16, 2012|website=YouTube|access-date=January 18, 2017}}</ref> [[Billie Holiday]], the [[Spice Girls]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/features/29/look-demi-lovato-reveals-her-first-love-was-spice |title=Look: Demi Lovato reveals her first love was The Spice Girls!|publisher= [[Myx]] |author=Karen Jane Ng |date=September 30, 2017 |accessdate=August 21, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190821080025/https://myx.abs-cbn.com/features/29/look-demi-lovato-reveals-her-first-love-was-spice |archivedate=August 21, 2019}}</ref> and [[Billy Gilman]].<ref name=\"influences\"/> About Gilman she said, \"We had the same voice range when I was young. I would practice to his songs all the time.\"<ref name=\"houstonchronicle\">{{cite web|author=Joey Guerra|title=Demi Lovato: Texas' own 'tween star|url=http://www.chron.com/life/article/Demi-Lovato-Texas-own-tween-star-1792031.php|work=[[Houston Chronicle]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 19, 2008}}</ref> Lovato listened to [[Heavy metal music|metal music]] in her teens<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1593780/demi-lovato-metalhead-plus-dillinger-escape-plan-dragonforce-more-news-that-rules-in-metal-file/|title=Demi Lovato metalhead?|author=Chris Harris|work=MTV News|publisher=Viacom|date=August 29, 2008|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref> and has said that [[John Mayer]]'s songwriting has been a \"huge influence\" on her and that after the release of ''Unbroken,'' her musical style shifted towards [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]].<ref name=\"influences\" />\n\nLovato says, \"I had a lot of respect for [[Whitney Houston]], and Christina Aguilera, on some songs where she was really amazing and wasn't trying to be sexy or anything like that.\"<ref>{{cite web|title = Demi Lovato Q&A: On 'Demi,' Her 'X Factor' Return and Being Sick of Party Songs|url = https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/1561404/demi-lovato-qa-on-demi-her-x-factor-return-and-being-sick-of-party|accessdate = September 21, 2015}}</ref> About her admiration for Clarkson, Lovato says, \"I just thought she was a great role model. She was never publicly seen drinking and driving or wearing really scandalous clothes or anything like that. I feel like she set a really great example and she was extremely talented.\"<ref>{{cite journal | last = Nguyen | first = Vi-An | url = http://parade.com/40734/viannguyen/25-demi-lovato-i-want-to-settle-down-in-the-next-few-years/ | title = Demi Lovato: I Want to 'Settle Down' in the Next Few Years | journal = Parade | date = March 25, 2013 | accessdate = April 17, 2014 }}</ref> Lovato's [[The Neon Lights Tour]] was \"inspired by [[Beyonc\u00e9]].\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Garibaldi|first=Christina|title=Demi Lovato Will Make Like Queen Bey On Neon Lights Tour|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1721955/demi-lovato-nick-jonas-neon-lights-tour/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=February 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Voice===\nNick Levine of ''[[Digital Spy]]'', commenting on her vocals for her album, ''[[Don't Forget]],'' stated, \"she's certainly a stronger singer than the [[Jonas Brothers|Jonases]]. In fact, her full-bodied vocal performances are consistently impressive.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/review/a154015/demi-lovato-dont-forget.html|title=Demi Lovato: 'Don't Forget'|author=Nick Levine|work=Digital Spy|date=April 26, 2009|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref> Becky Brain of [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] wrote that Lovato has a \"killer voice and the A-list material to put it to good use.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Brain|first=Becky|title=Demi Lovato 'Unbroken': Fall Preview|url=http://idolator.com/5996492/demi-lovato-unbroken-fall-music-preview|publisher=Idolator. Buzz Media|accessdate=September 16, 2011|date=September 7, 2011}}</ref> According to Sophie Schillaci of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', the entertainer \"has a voice that can silence even the harshest of critics. Something not often found in her peers.\"<ref>{{cite news|author= Sophie Schillaci|title=Demi Lovato at The Greek: Concert Review|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/demi-lovato-concert-review-x-factor-greek-351436|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=July 19, 2012}}</ref>\nFor Lovato's second studio album, ''Here We Go Again'', Jeff Miers from ''The Buffalo News'' wrote, \"Unlike so many of her Disney-fied peers, Lovato can really sing...[and it's] refreshing [she doesn't need [[Auto-Tune]]] to mask any lack of natural ability.\"<ref name=\"Buffalo News\">{{cite news|url=http://www.buffalonews.com/incoming/article5800.ece |title=Demi Lovato shows her talents on new disc |date=July 31, 2009 |work=[[The Buffalo News]] |publisher=[[Berkshire Hathaway]] |last=Miers |first=Jeff |accessdate=October 9, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120630053744/http://www.buffalonews.com/incoming/article5800.ece |archivedate=June 30, 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nUpon working with Lovato on her third studio album, ''Unbroken'', [[Ryan Tedder]] stated, \"Demi blew me out of the water vocally! I had no idea how good her voice is. She's one of the best singers I've ever worked with. Literally, that good... I mean, she's a Kelly Clarkson-level vocalist. And Kelly has a set of pipes.\" He also commented on their work together on the song \"Neon Lights\" from Lovato's fourth studio album, saying, \"She, in pop music, has one of the biggest ranges, possibly the highest full voice singer I've ever worked with.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/onerepublic/news/ryan-tedder-demi-lovato-video/|title=OneRepublic's Ryan Tedder Hails Demi Lovato's Voice And \"Incredible\" Range \u2013 Video|date=October 12, 2013|work=Capital|accessdate=November 3, 2014}}</ref> Tamsyn Wilce from Alter the Press commented on her vocals on ''Demi'', stating \"it shows just how strong her vocal cords are and the variation of styles that she can completely work to make her own.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alterthepress.com/2013/05/atp-album-review-demi-lovato-demi.html|title=Alter The Press!: ATP! Album Review: Demi Lovato \u2013 Demi|publisher=|accessdate=November 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn a review for the Neon Lights Tour, Mike Wass from Idolator commented \"you don't need shiny distractions when you can belt out songs like Demi and connect with the crowd on such an emotional level.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7505188/demi-lovato-neon-lights-tour-review-setlist|title=Demi Lovato's 'Neon Lights' Tour Shines Bright In Vancouver, Canada: Live Review \u2013 Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on Idolator.com|work=Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on Idolator.com|accessdate=November 3, 2014}}</ref>\nIn a review for the Demi World Tour, Marielle Wakim from ''Los Angeles Magazine'' commented on Lovato's vocals, stating, \"For those who haven't bothered to follow Lovato's career, let's get something out of the way: the girl can sing. Get over your fear of being judged by your Facebook friends and Spotify her discography, because you're going to have the last laugh five years down the road (probably sooner) when she wins a Grammy. At 22 years old, her vocal range is astounding.\" She went on to further describe her vocals as \"spectacular.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lamag.com/culturefiles/need-shelf-pride-start-listening-demi-lovato|title=Music: If You're Not Listening to Demi Lovato, You're Doing it Wrong \u2013 Los Angeles Magazine|work=Los Angeles Magazine|accessdate=November 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\nLovato was praised for her performance of \"[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]\" at [[Super Bowl LIV]]. Patrick Ryan of ''[[USA Today]]'' applauded Lovato for delivering a \"flawless performance\" and \"reminding us she's one of the best vocalists in the industry today.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/music/2020/02/02/demi-lovatos-super-bowl-national-anthem/4641831002/|title=Demi Lovato wows with flawless, confident national anthem at Super Bowl|last=Ryan|first=Patrick|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> He went on to note that she \"she hit all the high notes with ease\" and ultimately \"even added some of her own riffs\" which he says resulted in \"a rendition that was uniquely and phenomenally hers.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/music/2020/02/02/demi-lovatos-super-bowl-national-anthem/4641831002/|title=Demi Lovato wows with flawless, confident national anthem at Super Bowl|last=Ryan|first=Patrick|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n===Residence===\nOn her 18th birthday, Lovato bought a Mediterranean-style house in [[Los Angeles, California]] for her family; however, she decided to live in a \"[[sober house]]\" in Los Angeles after leaving rehab in January 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mstarz.com/articles/7562/20130111/demi-lovato-likes-sober-move-addiction-again.htm|title=Demi Lovato Likes To Be Sober And Not Move Into Addiction Again, Makes Sober House Her Home|publisher=Mstarz|date=January 11, 2013|access-date=March 1, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306125523/http://www.mstarz.com/articles/7562/20130111/demi-lovato-likes-sober-move-addiction-again.htm|archive-date=March 6, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> In September 2016, Lovato also purchased a Laurel Canyon home in Los Angeles for $8.3 million, but is in the process of selling the house.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://observer.com/2018/09/demi-lovato-home-for-sale-laurel-canyon-hollywood-hills-overdose/|title=Demi Lovato Is Selling the $9.5 Million Hollywood Hills Home Where She Overdosed|date=2018-09-05|website=Observer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> \n\n===Hobbies===\nLovato started training in [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu]] in 2016.<ref>{{cite AV media|last=Demi Lovato|title=Demi Lovato Does Jiu Jitsu|date=October 10, 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J1E0RCW1yT0|accessdate=October 11, 2017}}</ref> {{asof|2019}} she is ranked a [[BJJ belt|blue belt]] in the martial art, which is derived from [[jujutsu]].<ref>[https://people.com/health/demi-lovato-earned-new-jiu-jitsu-degree/amp/ Demi Lovato Earned a New Degree in Jiu-Jitsu: 'This Means the World to Me'] Julie Mazziotta, [[People (magazine)|People]], March 21, 2019</ref>\n\n===Relationships===\nLovato had no interest in forging a relationship with her late father, Patrick, after his divorce from her mother.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fabulousmag.co.uk/2012/04/22/the-fame-the-drugs-the-self-harm/|title=The fame, the drugs, the self-harm|last=Hoyle|first=Antonia|date=April 22, 2012|website=Fabulous|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101094046/http://fabulousmag.co.uk/2012/04/22/the-fame-the-drugs-the-self-harm/|archivedate=November 1, 2012|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref> She has been vocal about her abusive and strained relationship with her father and once stated, \"He was mean, but he wanted to be a good person. And he wanted to have his family, and when my mom married my stepdad, he still had this huge heart where he said, 'I'm so glad that [he's] taking care of you and doing the job that I wish I could do'.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/174362_demi_lovato_opens_up_about_her_abusive_father_patrick_lovato/|title=Demi Lovato Opens Up About Her 'Abusive' Father: 'I Was Very Conflicted When He Passed'|last=Bueno|first=Antoinette|date=October 20, 2015|work=[[Entertainment Tonight|Entertainment Tonight Online]]|accessdate=February 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/10/22/demi-lovato-talks-about-her-relationship-with-her-father.html|title=Demi Lovato talks about her relationship with her father|date=October 22, 2015|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=February 27, 2017}}</ref> Patrick died of cancer on June 22, 2013, at age 53.<ref name=\"Cover\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/27/showbiz/celebrity-news-gossip/demi-lovato-father-mental-illness|title=Demi Lovato speaks on dad's death|date=June 27, 2013|accessdate=June 28, 2013|publisher=[[CNN]]}}</ref> After his death, Lovato said that he had been mentally ill, and in his honor she created the Lovato Treatment Scholarship Program.<ref name=\"Lovece\" />\n\nLovato had an [[On-again, off-again relationship|on-off relationship]] with American singer [[Joe Jonas]] between 2008 and 2010, but they prioritized their friendship.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Michaels|first1=Wendy|title=Did Demi Lovato & Joe Jonas Date? 'Tell Me You Love Me' Singer Opens Up About Their Past|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/did-demi-lovato-joe-jonas-date-tell-me-you-love-me-singer-opens-up-about-their-past-2890123|accessdate=March 7, 2018|website=[[Elite Daily]]|date=October 11, 2017}}</ref> From 2010 to 2016, she was in a relationship with actor [[Wilmer Valderrama]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.com.au/demi-lovato-says-boyfriend-wilmer-valderrama-supported-her-recovery-she-wouldnt-be-alive-without-him |title=Demi Lovato Says Boyfriend Wilmer Valderrama 'Supported Her Recovery' And 'She Wouldn't Be Alive Without Him'|newspaper=[[International Business Times]]|first=Sonalee|last=Singh|date=March 18, 2015|accessdate=October 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.etonline.com/news/180546_wilmer_valderrama_talks_about_loving_demi_lovato_only_when_the_timing_was_right/ |title=Wilmer Valderrama Reveals Secret to Demi Lovato Relationship: I Loved Her 'Exactly When She Needs Me to Love Her'|website=[[Entertainment Tonight|Entertainment Tonight Online]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|location=Chicago, Illinois|date=January 21, 2016 |accessdate=June 4, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/770197/demi-lovato-and-wilmer-valderrama-break-up-after-almost-6-years-of-dating|title=Demi Lovato and Wilmer Valderrama Break Up After Nearly 6 Years of Dating|website=[[E! Online]]|date=June 3, 2016|accessdate=June 4, 2016}}</ref> Lovato later in 2016 dated professional [[mixed martial artist]] and former [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC) middleweight champion [[Luke Rockhold]] for a few months.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://generationiron.com/luke-rockhold-discusses-demi-lovato-fun/|title=Luke Rockhold On Ex Demi Lovato: \"It was Fun For Me And She's Still A Nice Girl\"|last=Bell|first=Nicholas|date=February 9, 2018|website=Generation Iron Fitness & Bodybuilding Network|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref> She also enjoyed a brief romance with [[mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] fighter Guilherme \"Bomba\" Vasconcelos until May 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=Demi Lovato Splits From MMA Fighter Guilherme ''Bomba'' Vasconcelos |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/849323/demi-lovato-splits-from-mma-fighter-guilherme-bomba-vasconcelos |website=E! |date=May 8, 2017}}</ref> In late 2018, Lovato dated fashion designer [[Henri Alexander Levy]] until early 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1021134/demi-lovato-and-henry-levy-break-up|title=Demi Lovato and Henry Levy Break Up|date=March 6, 2019|website=E!|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref> Most recently, she split from model Austin Wilson, after a few months of dating and publicizing her relationship in November 2019.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://people.com/music/demi-lovato-austin-wilson-split-after-months-of-dating/|title=Demi Lovato and Austin Wilson Split After Months of Dating: 'She's Concentrating on Herself'|magazine=People|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref> Lovato describes her sexuality as fluid, and has said she is open to finding love with someone of any gender.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/919029/demi-lovato-is-happily-single-and-ready-to-slide-into-your-dms|title=Demi Lovato Is Happily Single\u2014and Ready to Slide Into Your DMs|last=Johnson|first=Zach|date=March 7, 2018|website=[[E!]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1118008/demi-lovato-reveals-the-really-beautiful-moment-she-came-out-to-her-parents|title=Demi Lovato Reveals the \"Really Beautiful\" Moment She Came Out to Her Parents|last=Aiello|first=McKenna|date=January 30, 2020|website=[[E!]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Health===\nLovato had suffered from [[depression (mood disorder)|depression]], an [[eating disorder]], [[self-harm]], and being [[bullying|bullied]] before she went into rehab at the age of 18.<ref name=PunchApology/><ref>{{cite web|first=Peter|last=Gicas|title=Demi Lovato Still Has \"Nightmares\" About the Childhood Bullying She Endured |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/434771/demi-lovato-still-has-nightmares-about-the-childhood-bullying-she-endured|work=[[E! Online]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|location=New York City|accessdate=December 27, 2015|date=June 28, 2013}}</ref> On November 1, 2010, Lovato withdrew from the [[Jonas Brothers Live in Concert World Tour 2010|Jonas Brothers Live in Concert]] tour, entering a treatment facility for \"physical and emotional issues\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/208889/demi-lovato-enters-treatment-center-for-issues|title=Demi Lovato Enters Treatment Center for 'Issues'|first=Natalie|last=Finn|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|location=New York City|date=November 1, 2010|accessdate=March 14, 2010}}</ref> It was reported<ref name=\"ussales\">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/podcasts/7423955/hozier-ask-pop-shop-podcast|title=Pop Shop Podcast: Hozier Talks 'Better Love' & What's Next, Plus Burning Questions About Britney, Demi & More|last1=Atkinson|first1=Katie|date=July 5, 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160706161316/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/podcasts/7423955/hozier-ask-pop-shop-podcast|archivedate=July 6, 2016|last2=Caulfield|first2=Keith}}</ref> that she decided to enter treatment after punching female dancer [[Beat Freaks#Alex Welch|Alex Welch]]; her management and family convinced her she needed help. Lovato said she took \"100 percent, full responsibility\" for the incident.<ref name=PunchApology>{{cite news|first=Janice|last=Johnston|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/demi-lovato-interview-teen-star-opens-bulimia-cutting/story?id=13405090&page=1|title=Demi Lovato Interview: Teen Star Opens Up on Bulimia, Cutting Issues|website=[[ABC News]]|publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company]]|location=New York City|date=April 19, 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110521143956/http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/demi-lovato-interview-teen-star-opens-bulimia-cutting/story?id=13405090&page=1|archivedate=May 21, 2011|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref> On January 28, 2011, Lovato completed inpatient treatment at Timberline Knolls and returned home. She acknowledged that she had [[bulimia]], had harmed herself, and had been \"self-medicating\" with drugs and alcohol \"like a lot of teens do to numb their pain\".<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Ellen|last=Collis|title=Demi Lovato Exclusive Interview|url=http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/g2206/exclusive-interview-demi-lovato/|magazine=[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]|publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]]|location=New York City|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref> She added that she \"basically had a [[nervous breakdown]]\" and was diagnosed with [[bipolar disorder]] during her treatment.<ref>{{cite news|title=Disney Star Demi Lovato: I'm Bipolar|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2011/04/20/disney-star-demi-lovato-im-bipolar/|website=[[Fox News Channel]]|publisher=[[News Corporation (1980\u20132013)|News Corp.]]|location=New York City|date=April 20, 2011|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref> Lovato later said that she had used [[cocaine]] several times a day and smuggled cocaine onto airplanes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/videos/demi-lovato-admits-i-would-smuggle-cocaine-on-airplanes-exclusive-43141/ |title=Demi Lovato Admits: I Would 'Smuggle' Cocaine On Airplanes (Exclusive)|website=[[Access Hollywood]]|accessdate=December 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Demi Lovato at the Democratic National Convention, July 2016 (cropped C).jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato speaking at the [[2016 Democratic National Convention]] in Philadelphia on July 25, 2016]]\nIn April 2011, Lovato became a contributing editor for ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]'' magazine, writing an article that described her struggles.<ref name=\"Seventeen2011\">{{cite news|url=https://www.seventeen.com/health/advice/g2102/demi-lovato-pressure-to-be-perfect/ |title=Demi Lovato Opens Up About the Pressure to Be Perfect |magazine=[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]] |publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]] |location=New York City|date=April 14, 2011 |accessdate=April 19, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110417050727/http://www.seventeen.com/health/tips/demi-lovato-hub |archivedate=April 17, 2011 |df= }}</ref> In March 2012, [[MTV]] aired a documentary, ''[[Demi Lovato: Stay Strong]]'', about her rehab and recovery.<ref>{{cite web|first=X.|last=Alexander|url=http://idolator.com/6210151/demi-lovatos-stay-strong-documentary-watch|title=Demi Lovato's 'Stay Strong' Documentary: Watch|website=[[Idolator (blog)|Idolator]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|location=San Francisco, California|date=March 7, 2012|accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref> She began work on her fourth album the following month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sawfnews.com/Entertainment/68532.aspx|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407232620/http://www.sawfnews.com/Entertainment/68532.aspx|title=Demi Lovato Starts Work on Her Fourth Album|publisher=Sawfnews. [[WordPress]]|date=April 5, 2012|archivedate=April 7, 2012|accessdate=November 1, 2012}}</ref> In January 2013, it was reported that Lovato had been living in a [[sober living environment|sober-living facility]] in Los Angeles for more than a year because she felt it was the best way to avoid returning to her addictions and eating disorder.<ref name=\"Time Warner\">{{cite web|title=Demi Lovato: The Sober Living House Is My Home!|url=https://www.tmz.com/2013/01/11/demi-lovato-sober-living-house-home-x-factor/|website=[[TMZ]]|publisher=[[Time Warner]]|location=New York City|accessdate=January 24, 2013|date=January 11, 2013}}</ref> Lovato celebrated the six year anniversary of her [[sobriety]] on March 15, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aniftos|first1=Rania|title=Demi Lovato Celebrates 5-Year Anniversary of Her Sobriety|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7727833/demi-lovato-celebrates-five-years-sobriety|accessdate=March 15, 2017|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=March 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn her 2017 [[YouTube]] documentary ''Demi Lovato: Simply Complicated'', Lovato revealed publicly that her treatment at Timberline Knolls was not entirely successful, stating that she still struggled with [[alcoholism]] and a [[cocaine addiction]] in the year following her stint in the treatment centre and further revealing that she was in fact under the influence of cocaine while being interviewed about her sobriety for ''Demi Lovato: Stay Strong''.<ref name=\"Simply Complicated\">{{cite web|title=Demi Lovato: Simply Complicated \u2013 Official Documentary|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZWTlL_w8cRA|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=October 21, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"SC Billboard\"/><ref name=\"SC Maxim\"/><ref name=\"SC InStyle\"/> She stated: \"I wasn't working my program. I wasn't ready to get sober. I was sneaking it on planes, sneaking it in bathrooms, sneaking it throughout the night. Nobody knew.\"<ref name=\"SC Billboard\">{{cite news|last1=Armstrong|first1=Megan|title=The 10 Most Honest Confessions From Demi Lovato's 'Simply Complicated' YouTube Documentary|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8005791/demi-lovato-simply-complicated-documentary-youtube-best-moments|accessdate=October 22, 2017|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\nLovato also stated that her drug and alcohol addictions caused her to not only nearly [[overdose]] several times, but later began to impact her ability to perform and promote her third studio album ''[[Unbroken (Demi Lovato album)|Unbroken]]'', referencing a 2012 performance on the [[American Idol (season 11)|eleventh season]] of ''[[American Idol]]'' where she was severely [[hangover|hungover]].<ref name=\"Simply Complicated\"/><ref name=\"SC Maxim\">{{cite news|title=Demi Lovato Talks About Casual Sex and Cocaine Addiction in Her Revealing 'Simply Complicated'|url=https://www.maxim.com/women/demi-lovato-talks-cocaine-casual-sex-simply-complicated-2017-10|accessdate=October 22, 2017|magazine=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]|publisher=[[Biglari Holdings]]|location=San Antonio, Texas|date=October 22, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"SC InStyle\">{{cite news|last1=Fowler|first1=Brandi|title=Demi Lovato's Childhood Bullies Were So Intense They Petitioned for Her Suicide|url=http://www.instyle.com/news/demi-lovato-simply-complicated-documentary-interview|magazine=[[InStyle]]|date=October 17, 2017|accessdate=October 22, 2017}}</ref> After her management team had expressed their intentions to leave her, Lovato agreed to resume treatment and counseling for her addictions, leading to her move to a sober-living facility in Los Angeles with roommates and responsibilities to help her overcome her drug and alcohol problems.<ref name=\"Simply Complicated\"/><ref name=\"SC InStyle\"/>\n\n==== 2018 overdose ====\nOn June 21, 2018, Lovato released \"[[Sober (Demi Lovato song)|Sober]]\" in which she revealed she had relapsed after six years of sobriety.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nick|last=Romano|url=https://ew.com/music/2018/06/21/demi-lovato-sober-song-video/|title=Demi Lovato confesses 'I'm not sober anymore' in new song|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=June 21, 2018|accessdate=July 28, 2018}}</ref> On July 24, 2018, she was rushed to the [[Cedars-Sinai Medical Center]] in Los Angeles after emergency services were called to her home due to an [[opioid overdose]].<ref name=\"cnn\" /><ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite web |title=Demi Lovato addresses addiction battle |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-45079386 |website=[[BBC News]] |publisher=[[BBC]]|location=London, England|date=August 6, 2018|accessdate=August 9, 2018 }}</ref> She was reported to be stable and recovering later in the day.<ref name=\"cnn\">{{Cite news|first1=Sandra|last1=Gonzalez|first2=Chloe|last2=Melas|first3=Lisa|last3=Respers France|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/07/24/entertainment/demi-lovato-hospitalized/index.html|title=Demi Lovato stable and recovering after apparent overdose|website=[[CNN]]|publisher=[[Turner Broadcasting Systems]]|location=Atlanta, Georgia|date=July 24, 2018|access-date=July 27, 2018}}</ref> Lovato was reported to have overdosed on [[oxycodone]] laced with [[fentanyl]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ross |first1=Martha |title=Demi Lovato's overdose likely caused by drug laced with fentanyl, report says |url=https://www.mercurynews.com/2018/08/14/demi-lovatos-overdose-likely-caused-by-fentanyl-opioid-report-says/ |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |work=San Jose Mercury News |date=August 14, 2018}}</ref> and was revived with [[naloxone]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ryan |first1=Lisa |title=Demi Lovato Will Reportedly Be in Rehab for Several Months |url=https://www.thecut.com/2018/08/demi-lovato-drug-overdose-tmz-report.html |website=The Cut |accessdate=October 18, 2018|date=August 14, 2018}}</ref> She was hospitalized for two weeks and subsequently entered an in-patient rehab facility.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8468762/demi-lovato-released-from-hospital-enters-in-patient-facility-report|title=Demi Lovato Released From Hospital, Enters In-Patient Facility: Report|website=Billboard|access-date=January 4, 2019}}</ref> In December 2018, Lovato took to [[Twitter]] to dismiss rumors about her overdose and went on to thank her fans, writing: \"If I feel like the world needs to know something, I will tell them MYSELF. All my fans need to know is I'm working hard on myself, I'm happy and clean and I'm SO grateful for their support.\"<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|first=Bonnie|last=Steirnberg|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8491314/demi-lovato-recovery-response-twitter|title=Demi Lovato Responds to Rumors About Her Recovery|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=January 4, 2019}}</ref> She went on to add that some day she will \"tell the world what exactly happened, why it happened and what my life is like today.. but until I'm ready to share that with people please stop prying and making up shit that you know nothing about. I still need space and time to heal.\"<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/> \n\nLovato later revealed on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''  that her worsened struggles with bulimia in 2018 contributed to her eventual drug overdose, as she relapsed three months prior to the incident due to being extremely unhappy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/snyde/ny-demi-lovato-discusses-relapse-sobriety-20200305-6tn3b2xpgva75gaoj4r6yomglm-story.html|title=Demi Lovato reveals what led to her 2018 overdose|last=Ganz|first=Jami|website=nydailynews.com|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> Lovato attributed these struggles to the extreme measures that her former manager, Phil McIntyre, took to control what she ate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/artists/demi-lovato/news/manager-phil-mcintyre-eating-disorder-i-love-me/|title=Demi Lovato says her old manager used to \"control\" what she ate|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> Lovato also explained that, along with the controlling nature of her management team, they did not provide her with the help she needed: \"People checking what my orders at Starbucks were on my bank statements... just little things like that... it led me to being really unhappy and my bulimia got really bad and I asked for help and I didn't receive the help that I needed.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/artists/demi-lovato/news/manager-phil-mcintyre-eating-disorder-i-love-me/|title=Demi Lovato says her old manager used to \"control\" what she ate|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> In the same interview, Lovato revealed that her thought process on the night she relapsed following six years of sobriety was as follows: \"I'm six years sober and I'm miserable. I'm even more miserable than I was when I was drinking. Why am I sober?\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/artists/demi-lovato/news/manager-phil-mcintyre-eating-disorder-i-love-me/|title=Demi Lovato says her old manager used to \"control\" what she ate|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>  When Lovato confronted her management team about her thoughts, they responded with \"'You're being very selfish, this would ruin things for not just you but for us as well,\" which she says made her feel \"completely abandoned\" due to triggering her underlying abandonment issues with her birth father, and so she \"drank that night\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/artists/demi-lovato/news/manager-phil-mcintyre-eating-disorder-i-love-me/|title=Demi Lovato says her old manager used to \"control\" what she ate|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n==Activism==\nLovato is a supporter of [[LGBT rights]]. When the [[Defense of Marriage Act]] was appealed in June 2013, Lovato celebrated the occasion on Twitter, tweeting: \"[[Gay]], [[Heterosexuality|straight]], [[lesbian]], [[bisexuality|bi]].&nbsp;... No one is better than any one else. What an incredible day for California AND for equality.\"<ref name=LoveIsLove>{{cite web|last=Blake|first=Emily|title=Lady Gaga, Demi Lovato Proclaim '#LoveIsLove' After Gay-Marriage Ruling|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1709619/supreme-court-gay-marriage-ruling-celebrity-reactions/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=June 26, 2013}}</ref> Lovato later said: \"I believe in [[gay marriage]], I believe in equality. I think there's a lot of hypocrisy with religion. But I just found that you can have your own relationship with God, and I still have a lot of faith.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Tang|first=Vivian|title=Demi's New Image? \"[Neon Lights] Was My Grown-Up Sexy Video\"|url=http://www.cambio.com/2013/11/22/demis-new-image-neon-lights-was-my-grown-up-sexy-video/|publisher=Cambio|accessdate=November 24, 2013|date=November 22, 2013}}</ref> Lovato later filmed her music video for [[Really Don't Care]] at the [[Los Angeles Pride|LA Pride Parade]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6140783/demi-lovato-really-dont-care-video-cher-lloyd-los-angeles-pride|title=Demi Lovato & Cher Lloyd's 'Really Don't Care' Video: Demi Invade L.A. Pride|date=2014-06-26|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> For her advocacy efforts on behalf of the LGBT community, Lovato was awarded the Vanguard Award at the [[GLAAD]] (formerly the Gay & Lesbian Alliance Against Defamation) in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/07/25/demi-lovato-sexuality-addiction-mental-illness-lgbt-icon/|title=This is why Demi Lovato is an LGBT icon|date=2018-07-25|website=PinkNews - Gay news, reviews and comment from the world's most read lesbian, gay, bisexual, and trans news service|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> When Lovato went on stage to accept her award, she said it meant \"more than any music award\" and teared up when talking about growing up in Texas, \"where it wasn\u2019t very accepting of any sort of LGBT person\" and growing up with \"friends that were gay and were afraid to come out\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/07/25/demi-lovato-sexuality-addiction-mental-illness-lgbt-icon/|title=This is why Demi Lovato is an LGBT icon|date=2018-07-25|website=PinkNews - Gay news, reviews and comment from the world's most read lesbian, gay, bisexual, and trans news service|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> \n\nOn December 23, 2011, Lovato posted a message on [[Twitter]] criticizing her former network for airing episodes of ''[[Shake It Up (U.S. TV series)|Shake It Up]]'' and ''[[So Random!]]'' in which characters joked about [[eating disorder]]s. [[Disney Channel]] publicity officials quickly took action, apologizing to Lovato and removing the episodes from the network's broadcast and [[video on demand]] sources after additional criticism (following Lovato's post) on the network's public-relations account.<ref name=\"SlamDisney\">{{cite news|first=Jessica|last=Derschowitz|title=Demi Lovato slams Disney Channel over eating disorder joke|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/demi-lovato-slams-disney-channel-over-eating-disorder-joke/|publisher=CBS News|date=December 26, 2011|accessdate=December 26, 2011}}</ref>\n\nLovato identifies as a [[feminism|feminist]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Chima |last=Simone |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/567636/demi-lovato-gets-feminism-right-see-the-celebs-that-have-gotten-it-all-wrong |title=Demi Lovato Gets Feminism Right, See the Celebs That Have Gotten It All Wrong! |date=August 8, 2014 |publisher=[[E! Online]] |accessdate=May 31, 2015}}</ref> Lovato explained what the term means to her in an interview with [[Dolly (magazine)|''Dolly'' (magazine)]] in 2017, saying \"Feminism means to me doesn\u2019t have to mean burning bras and hating men, what feminism means to me is just standing up for gender equality and trying to empower our youth. And showing women that you can embrace your sexuality and you deserve to have confidence and you don\u2019t need to conform to society\u2019s views on what women should be or how you should dress. So, I think it is just about supporting other women and empowering other women.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dolly.com.au/dolly-doctor/demi-lovato-exclusively-talks-to-dolly-15164|title=Demi Lovato talks about feminism and cyber-bullying|last=Galea|first=Matt|website=Dolly|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nLovato spoke at the [[2016 Democratic National Convention]] in Philadelphia about raising awareness for mental health,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/biz/news/demi-lovato-democratic-national-convention-1201822654/|title=Demi Lovato Performs AT DNC, Talks Mental Health Care|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=September 30, 2016|last=Johnson|first=Ted|date=July 25, 2016}}</ref> and also performed at the [[March for Our Lives]] anti-gun violence rally in Washington, D.C. in March 2018.<ref name=\"CBS\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x1XfTAoS7hg \"Demi Lovato Performs At March For Our Lives In Washington, D.C.\"]. CBS Miami. (March 24, 2018).</ref><ref name=\"MP\">Maria Pasquini. [http://people.com/music/demi-lovato-miley-cyrus-march-for-our-lives/ \"Demi Lovato and Miley Cyrus Reunite at March for Our Lives: 'Happy to Stand with You'\"]. People Music (May 2, 2017).</ref>\n\nIn October 2019, Lovato attended a free trip to [[Israel]] provided by the Ministry of Jerusalem Affairs and private donors,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://forward.com/schmooze/432703/demi-lovato-went-on-a-150k-trip-to-israel-paid-for-by-israel-and-private/|title=Demi Lovato Went On A Trip To Israel--Paid For By Israel and Private Funders|last=Singer|first=Jenny|date=October 7, 2019|website=Forward|language=en-US|access-date=January 27, 2020}}</ref> where she was baptised in the [[Jordan River]]. After posting pictures on [[Instagram]], she immediately received backlash due to the [[Israeli\u2013Palestinian conflict]], but later insisted that it was meant to be a spiritual experience, not a political statement.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-israel-sponcon-apology-895137/|title=Demi Lovato Apologizes for Accepting Controversial Trip to Israel|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=October 4, 2019|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=October 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\n[[File:Demi Lovato May 2013.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Lovato at the [[Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration|SAMHSA]]'s [[National Children's Mental Health Awareness Week|National Children's Mental Health Awareness Day]] on May 7, 2013]]\nIn May 2009, Lovato was named an Honorary Ambassador of Education by the American Partnership For [[Eosinophilia|Eosinophilic]] Disorders.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://crushable.com/entertainment/demi-lovato-accepts-eosinophilic-honorary-ambassador-award/|title=Demi Lovato Accepts Eosinophilic Honorary Ambassador Award|publisher=Crushable|date=May 12, 2009|accessdate=March 16, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120531065317/http://crushable.com/entertainment/demi-lovato-accepts-eosinophilic-honorary-ambassador-award/|archive-date=May 31, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> As part of her involvement with Disney's Friends for Change, Lovato, the [[Jonas Brothers]], [[Miley Cyrus]] and [[Selena Gomez]] recorded the initiative's theme song (\"Send It On\") in 2009. The song debuted on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number 20,<ref name=\"iTunes\"/><ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite press release|url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2009/doc/Send_It_On_Disneys_Friends_for_Change%20_081909.doc |title=\"Send It On,\" an anthem by the world's biggest teen stars, Miley Cyrus, Jonas Brothers, Selena Gomez and Demi Lovato, for Disney's \"Friends for Change: Project Green,\" will debut on Radio Disney, Disney Channel, Disney.com and iTunes |date=August 6, 2009 |website=Disney Channel Media Net|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]] |location=Burbank, California|accessdate=August 20, 2009 |format=DOC |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110511155245/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2009/doc/Send_It_On_Disneys_Friends_for_Change%20_081909.doc |archivedate=May 11, 2011 }}</ref> and its proceeds were directed to environmental charities through the Disney Worldwide Conservation Fund.<ref name=\"pressrelease\" /> Lovato and Joe Jonas recorded another song, \"[[Make a Wave]]\", for the charity in March 2010.<ref name=\"iTunesMakeAWave\"/> She is also spokesperson for the Join the Surge Campaign!, DoSomething.Org and Joining the Surge by [[Clean & Clear]]; the latter is a national campaign encouraging teenagers to take action in their communities.<ref>{{cite pr|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/clean--clear-skincare-demi-lovato-and-dosomethingorg-join-forces-to-start-a-massive-movement-encouraging-teens-to-give-back-96372024.html|title=CLEAN & CLEAR\u00ae Skincare, Demi Lovato and DoSomething.org Join Forces to Start a Massive Movement Encouraging Teens to Give Back |publisher=[[PR Newswire]]|accessdate=December 27, 2015|date=June 15, 2010}}</ref>\n\nLovato was featured in a January 2010 public-service announcement for Voto Latino to promote the organization's \"Be Counted\" campaign preparing for the [[2010 United States Census]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://demilovatodaily.com/news.php?start_from=232&ucat=&archive=&subaction=&id=&|title=Voto Latino campaign, January 10, 2010|publisher=Demi Lovato Daily|accessdate=March 16, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160110220730/http://demilovatodaily.com/news.php?start_from=232&ucat=&archive=&subaction=&id=&|archive-date=January 10, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> In October 2010 she was the spokeswoman for the anti-bullying organization, PACER.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.pacer.org/bullying/about/pressrelease.asp?file=2010/nr20101001-1.asp|title=Demi Lovato, PACER and Facebook\u00ae Team Up to Stop Cyberbullying During National Bullying Prevention Month|publisher=National Bullying Prevention Center|date=October 1, 2010|accessdate=March 16, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130613100604/http://www.pacer.org/bullying/about/pressrelease.asp?file=2010/nr20101001-1.asp|archive-date=13 June 2013}}</ref> Lovato participated in the \"A Day Made Better\" school advocacy campaign<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsckids.com/2010/10/demi-lovato-does-a-day-made-better-school-advocacy-campaign/ |title=Demi Lovato Does 'A Day Made Better' School Advocacy Campaign |first=Sarah|last=Peel |website=BSCKids |date=October 7, 2010 |accessdate=March 16, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114143446/http://www.bsckids.com/2010/10/demi-lovato-does-a-day-made-better-school-advocacy-campaign/ |archivedate=November 14, 2012 }}</ref> and has supported [[DonateMyDress.org]], [[Kids Wish Network]], [[Love Our Children USA]], [[St. Jude Children's Research Hospital]] and [[City of Hope (charity)|City of Hope]].<ref name=\"Philanthropy\">{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/demi-lovato|title=Demi Lovato's Charity Work, Events and Causes|publisher=Look to the Stars: The World of Celebrity Giving|accessdate=March 10, 2013}}</ref> In April 2012 she became a contributing editor of ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]'' magazine, describing her personal struggles to its female teenage audience.<ref name=\"Seventeen2011\"/> She became a spokesperson for the anti-bullying organization PACER and appeared on ''[[America's Next Top Model]]'' to speak out against bullying.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oceanup.com/2010/09/02/demi-lovato-americas-next-top-model|title=Demi Lovato America's Next Top Model|publisher=Ocean Up. As If Productions|accessdate=July 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn October Lovato was named the ambassador of ''Mean Stinks'', a campaign focused on eliminating bullying by girls.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1694351/demi-lovato-mean-stinks-bullying/|title=Demi Lovato Tackling Girl-To-Girl Bullying, One 'Mean' Girl At A Time|author=Cory Midgarden|publisher=MTV News. Viacom|date=September 24, 2012|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref> In May 2013 she was cited for her dedication as a mentor to teens and young adults with mental-health problems at a National Children's Mental Health Awareness Day hosted by the [[Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration]] in Washington.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.medicaldaily.com/demi-lovato-honored-national-childrens-mental-health-awareness-day-event-245654|title=Demi Lovato Honored At National Children's Mental Health Awareness Day Event |publisher=Medicaldaily.com |date=May 8, 2013 |accessdate=August 22, 2013|first=Nadia-Elysse|last=Harris}}</ref> In late June 2013 Lovato announced the creation of the Lovato Treatment Scholarship Program, named for her late father, to pay treatment costs for mentally-ill patients.<ref name=\"Lovece\">{{cite news|url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/celebrities/demi-lovato-discusses-father-s-death-on-good-morning-america-1.5583327|title=Demi Lovato discusses father's death on 'Good Morning America'|last=Lovece|first=Frank|date=June 27, 2013|work=Newsday|accessdate=June 28, 2013}}</ref> In August 2013, she traveled to [[Kenya]] for her 21st birthday to participate in a program of the international charity organization [[Free the Children]].<ref name=\"Kenya2013\">{{cite web|last1=Nesbitt|first1=Cherylann|title=Demi Lovato Celebrates 21st Birthday In Kenya During Me to We Volunteer Trip|url=http://news.mtv.ca/blogs/we-day/demi-lovato-celebrates-21st-birthday-in-kenya-during-me-to-we-volunteer-trip/|website=MTV Canada|accessdate=April 5, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160521080749/http://news.mtv.ca/blogs/we-day/demi-lovato-celebrates-21st-birthday-in-kenya-during-me-to-we-volunteer-trip|archivedate=May 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, Lovato was named the LA Pride Parade Grand Marshal and the lead performer for NYC Pride Week for her contribution to the LGBT community. NYC Pride spokesperson Patti Diluigi said, \"Demi Lovato is an amazing role model for today's youth, both LGBT and non-LGBT, for her activism in the area of equality, positive messaging on body image, and level of openness with her struggles. As a community, we're fortunate to have an ally like Demi.\"<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.nycpride.org/uploads/press_releases/2014%20Pier%20Dance%20-%20Demi%20Release.pdf|work=NYC Pride|accessdate=May 6, 2014|date=May 5, 2014|title=MULTI-PLATINUM SELLING RECORDING ARTIST, DEMI LOVATO GOES BICOASTAL FOR PRIDE}}</ref> Lovato has also become the face of Human Rights Campaign's America's for Marriage Equality. For the announcement of the campaign, Lovato stated \"Whether you're LGBT or [[heterosexuality|straight]], your love is valid, beautiful and an incredible love. So let's protect love and strengthen the institution of marriage by allowing loving, caring and committed same-sex couples to legally marry. Please join me and the majority of American citizens who support marriage equality.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2014/07/demi-lovato-human-rights-campaign-marriage-equality|title=Demi Lovato Face of Human Rights Campaign's Americans for Marriage Equality \u2013 Fuse|work=Fuse|accessdate=August 26, 2015}}</ref> On April 2, 2016, Lovato received the [[GLAAD Vanguard Award]] for making a significant difference in promoting equal rights for the LGBT community at the [[27th GLAAD Media Awards]] ceremony.<ref name=\"GLAAD\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2016-glaad-media-award-winners-867481|title=GLAAD Media Awards: The Winners List|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=April 4, 2016|accessdate=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{as of|2015|September|}}, Lovato's name appears on the \"Unclaimed [[California Child Actor's Bill|Coogan]]\" list, which is a fund for child actors whose earnings were partially withheld, but which remain unclaimed by the former child performers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unclaimedcoogan.org/?q=applicants|title=unclaimed Coogan list|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304083142/http://www.unclaimedcoogan.org/?q=applicants|archivedate=March 4, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Demi Lovato (Red carpet) - Global Citizen Festival Hamburg 07.jpg|upright|left|thumb|Lovato at the [[Global Citizen Festival]] in [[Hamburg]], July 2017]]\nIn June 2016, Lovato was among the artists that signed an open letter to stop gun violence, created by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/open-letter/|title=An Open Letter to Congress from the Music Industry|accessdate=June 26, 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> That month, the [[Human Rights Campaign]] also released a video in tribute to the victims of the [[2016 Orlando nightclub shooting|2016 Orlando gay nightclub shooting]]; in the video, Lovato and others told the stories of the people killed there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hrc.org/blog/watch-49-celebrities-honor-49-victims-of-orlando-tragedy-in-new-ryan-murphy |title=49 Celebrities Honor 49 Victims of Orlando Tragedy &#124; Human Rights Campaign |publisher=Hrc.org |date= |accessdate=June 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Rothaus |first=Steve |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Pulse Orlando shooting scene a popular LGBT club where employees, patrons 'like family' |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/community/gay-south-florida/article83301677.html |work=The Miami Herald |access-date=June 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Lovato returned to Kenya to participate in working with [[We Day|We Movement]] to do work with women and children.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.refinery29.com/2017/01/136014/demi-lovato-africa-trip-charity|title=Demi Lovato Kenya Travel Pics We Movement Charity|date=January 13, 2017|accessdate=January 20, 2017|first=Morgan|last=Baila|work=Refinery29}}</ref> In March 2017, as a celebration of five-year anniversary of [[sobriety]], Lovato donated money to [[Los Angeles]]-based charities, randomly selecting a group of causes based on their work, which included [[Animal rights|animal]], [[LGBT rights|LGBT]] and adoption rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/837076/demi-lovato-celebrates-five-years-of-sobriety-by-hand-delivering-donations-to-charities|title=Demi Lovato Celebrates Five Years of Sobriety by Hand Delivering Donations to Charities|first=McKenna|last=Aiello|accessdate=March 21, 2017|date=March 19, 2017|publisher=[[Eonline.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.refinery29.com/2017/03/145949/demi-lovato-five-years-sober|title=Demi Lovato Celebrated Five Years Sober With A Selfless Act Of Kindness|last=de la Cretaz|first=Britni|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 21, 2017|publisher=[[Refinery29]]}}</ref> On March 22, Lovato will be honored with the Artistic Award of Courage at The Jane and Terry Semel Institute's biannual Open Mind Gala, which recognizes those who raise awareness and reduce the stigma of mental health issues.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7710060/demi-lovato-honored-mental-health-advocacy|title=Demi Lovato to be Honored for Mental Health Advocacy|last=Washington|first=Arlene|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=March 21, 2017|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard.com]]}}</ref>\n\nLovato partnered with [[Fabletics]] in May 2017 on limited edition activewear collection.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.instyle.com/news/demi-lovato-fabletics-collection-workout-clothes|title=Demi Lovato Is Launching an Activewear Collection with Fabletics|date=May 8, 2017|author=Kim Duong|magazine=InStyle}}</ref> The collaboration was in support of the United Nations Foundation's Girl Up campaign to fund programs \"for some of the world's most marginalized adolescent girls.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.com/fitness/Demi-Lovato-Fabletics-Collection-43514494|title=Brace Your Wallets: Fabletics Is Launching a Collaboration With Demi Lovato|date=May 12, 2017|author=Dominique Astorino|publisher=PopSugar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shape.com/fitness/clothes/demi-lovato-empower-young-girls-fabletics|title=Demi Lovato Teams Up with Fabletics to Empower Young Girls|date=May 8, 2017|author=Faith Brar|publisher=Shape.com}}</ref> On September 23, 2017, Lovato was named a [[Global Citizen (website)|Global Citizen]] ambassador for championing the mental health of thousands of children displaced within [[Iraq]] and other communities. Lovato and Global Citizen will fund the expansion of a [[Save the Children]] pilot program, Healing and Education through the Arts, to violence-scarred young people living around [[Kirkuk]] and [[Saladin Governorate]], Iraq.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/newswires/entertainment/demi-lovato-war-scarred-children-iraq-article-1.3516422|title=Demi Lovato to help war-scarred children in Iraq|accessdate=September 26, 2017|date=September 23, 2017|agency=Associated Press|publisher=[[nydailynews]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926143703/http://www.nydailynews.com/newswires/entertainment/demi-lovato-war-scarred-children-iraq-article-1.3516422|archivedate=September 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Demi Lovato discography|List of songs recorded by Demi Lovato|l2 = songs}}\n*''[[Don't Forget]]'' (2008)\n*''[[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato album)|Here We Go Again]]'' (2009)\n*''[[Unbroken (Demi Lovato album)|Unbroken]]'' (2011)\n*''[[Demi (album)|Demi]]'' (2013)\n*''[[Confident (album)|Confident]]'' (2015)\n*''[[Tell Me You Love Me (album)|Tell Me You Love Me]]'' (2017)\n<!-- THIS LIST IS FOR STUDIO ALBUMS ONLY; DO NOT ADD SOUNDTRACKS OR EP'S HERE. -->\n\n==Filmography==\n<!--DO NOT insert rowspans into these tables per WP:FILMOGRAPHY; they hinder accessibility-->\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Camp Rock]]''\n| Mitchie Torres\n| Television film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"